title: Bernstein rates DHL Group as 'Market-Perform'.
full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX Broker) - U.S. analyst firm Bernstein Research left its rating on DHL Group at "Market-Perform" with a price target of 43.50 euros. Even though the market is focused on DSV and DHL, there are more potential buyers for rail subsidiary DB Schenker, analyst Alexander Irving wrote in a research note published Thursday. The majority shareholders of Kühne+Nagel could also consider making an offer, as could shipping companies, which would have bulging coffers after the pandemic boom. With regard to DHL, the expert sees more implementation risks than he would like in the event of a takeover of DB Schenker./mis/edh  Publication of the original study: 30.08.2023 / 20:48 / UTC First disclosure of the original study: 31.08.2023 / 05:00 / UTC----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: ORPEA :  Oddo BHF maintains 'underperform' rating
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its 'Underperform' rating on Orpea shares, with an unchanged target price of 0.5 euros.Yesterday evening, the Group announced that it had sold 22 facilities in the Netherlands to Amvest Living & Care Fund for 85 million euros.Oddo BHF points out that the Netherlands accounted for just under 4% of the Group's revenues last year, and could therefore be considered a 'non-core' country. This decision should therefore have little impact on earnings in the short term, according to the analyst.'This news shows that the new strategy is being deployed, but we remain Underperform with an OC at 0.5 E, given the dilution effects linked to the Group's recapitalization', concludes the broker.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: BASTIDE :  Oddo BHF lowers its target price
full_text: Oddo BHF reaffirms its 'outperform' opinion on Bastide, with a price target lowered from 35 to 33 euros, in the wake of an adjustment to its forecasts for the healthcare provider, to take account in particular of rising financial costs.Bastide is considering allocating its capital to activities with higher margins and better ROCE, including divestments (ostomatherapy or MAD)", notes the analyst, who nonetheless considers that, in the meantime, the stock lacks short-term resilience. title: Airbus: share price rises, analyst upgrades to buy
full_text: Airbus shares gained nearly 1% at the end of the session, benefiting from a positive analysis by Stifel. The research consultancy resumed its monitoring of Airbus with a 'buy' recommendation and a price target of 165 euros, seeing it as "a key post-pandemic turnaround case over a decade, with attractive margin and cash flow, as well as a revaluation angle".The broker anticipates average annual growth of 20% in adjusted operating profit (EBIT) over the 2022-25 period, as well as an improvement in the conversion rate into FCF, thanks in particular to an improved mix of deliveries in the A320 family.According to Stifel, these above-consensus estimates are not reflected in the Airbus share price, which it believes is trading at a significant discount to its American peer Boeing, and only in line with its historical multiples.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. All rights reserved.

title: ERAMET :  AlphaValue remains 'light' with Gabon
full_text: On Wednesday, AlphaValue renewed its 'light' recommendation on Eramet, with a target price of 76.1 euros, following the coup d'état in Gabon, a country considered 'key' for the French mining group.In a research note, the research consultancy points out that Eramet produces 100% of its manganese in Gabon, noting in passing that the ore now accounts for 60% of its sales.Worse still, it adds, the metal now generates 90% of its current operating income (Ebitda) due to the difficulties currently being encountered by its nickel and mineralized sands activities.Bearing in mind that the country's borders have been closed, the independent consultancy believes that the company's performance should be expected to be affected by the political unrest in any case.'Whether it lasts for a few days or months, any climate of political instability in the country would only penalize the Group's results', it continues.The outcome of the coup is still uncertain, but its impact could be enormous", warns AlphaValue, which points out that the issue could weigh on the stock for some time, as markets tend to hate uncertainty.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: SAFRAN :  Stifel confirms its recommendation on the stock
full_text: Stifel maintains its 'Hold' rating on Safran shares, with an unchanged target price of 145 euros. The analyst believes that Safran is the dominant company in the narrow-body engine market via CFM International, the Safran/GE joint venture that captures nearly 70% of the market and remains the sole supplier of engines for the B-737 family.Despite modeling an average annual increase of 24% in adjusted EBIT between 2022 and 2025, Stifel remains 4% below consensus estimates, the broker claiming to be more cautious than consensus on the 'Propulsion' and 'Interiors' segments.  In our view, the current valuation accurately reflects the outlook for strong EBIT growth, but ignores Safran's habit of adding margin-diluting new businesses to its portfolio, which we are not particularly enthusiastic about," the broker says in essence. title: UBISOFT :  Oddo BHF remains cautious and 'neutral
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its 'neutral' rating on Ubisoft shares, with an unchanged target price of 27 euros. The analyst looks back in particular on the surprise created by Ubisoft last week with the announcement of a major agreement with Microsoft. The group is buying Activision's perpetual rights to distribute its current catalog of games in the cloud, as well as future games launched over the next 15 years.  The French company's content offering will thus be significantly enhanced (Activision posted sales of $8.5 billion last year, compared with $1.7 billion for Ubisoft), notably with the huge Call of Duty franchise", says Oddo BHF. Although the financial details of the agreement have not been disclosed, Oddo BHF believes that it could be a real 'game changer' if streaming succeeds in the industry. The broker is nevertheless cautious, pending validation of the agreement and better visibility on the development of this market segment. In the meantime, Oddo BHF believes that "the share price performance over the coming months will depend above all on demand for the games launched by Ubisoft". Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: EUROFINS SCIENTIFIC :  Deutsche Bank reduces its target price
full_text: Deutsche Bank announced on Tuesday that it had lowered its target price for Eurofins Scientific from €56 to €54, while reiterating its 'sell' recommendation on the stock.Having examined the accounts of the group's 280 European subsidiaries in order to gain a better understanding of its business model, the analyst deduced that the bio-analysis giant would need to significantly improve its performance across all its business lines in order to meet its 2027 targets.However, he points out, such a phenomenon has never occurred historically, with the sole exception of the Covid crisis, which gave the diagnostics industry a boost.'In view of these factors, we remain cautious as to the reality of such a major improvement', he stresses.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: FREELANCE.COM :  Stifel reduces its target price
full_text: While maintaining its 'hold' recommendation, Stifel has lowered its target price for Freelance.com from six to 4.9 euros, following the announcement of second-quarter sales 7% below the broker's forecast.Difficulties persist on the international front, while the slowdown in France proved more significant than expected, accounting for the bulk of this gap", according to Stifel, which has reduced its expectations for 2023 by 3.6% on sales and 9.4% on EPS.  The risk/return ratio remains unattractive, given the uncertainties surrounding the performance of international activities and the impact of the recently announced acquisition on activities in France", adds the broker.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: JCDECAUX :  Deutsche Bank raises its buy recommendation
full_text: On Friday, Deutsche Bank raised its recommendation on JCDecaux shares from "hold" to "buy", with an unchanged target price of 21 euros, indicating a potential upside of around 30%.In a note sent to its clients, Deutsche Bank stresses that it makes sense to buy the stock - which it considers a top-quality player in the media sector - when cyclical concerns begin to emerge."This is the case today", assures the German bank, which points out that the outdoor advertising specialist has underperformed the market by around 25% since March.While Deutsche Bank acknowledges that the group is exposed to the slowdown in Chinese growth, it considers that this factor is now well integrated into share prices.DB also believes that the staging of the Olympic Games in Paris next year could provide an additional source of revenue, while pointing out that its strong international presence represents a long-term growth lever, driven by digitalization, the purchase of online advertising space and sustainable development.The German bank adds that consolidation in the sector could also play a positive role, as it believes the French group is well placed for M&A transactions.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: AIR LIQUIDE :  Berenberg changes its recommendation to 'buy
full_text: Berenberg on Thursday upgraded its recommendation on Air Liquide shares to 'buy' from 'hold', with a price target raised from €165 to €178.In its research note, the German institution praises the industrial group's 'better-than-expected' operational discipline.The reason why we held a neutral opinion on Air Liquide for some time was our concern about possible over-investment in the highly fragmented hydrogen and ammonia segment", says the intermediary.Berenberg explains that it feared that this strategy would lead the Group to move away from its traditional business model based on take-or-pay contracts, so characteristic of the sector.'On the contrary, the last few quarters have shown that the company is paying attention to its investment policy, despite a strengthened balance sheet that could encourage it to multiply its spending', it concludes.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: CTS Eventim turn positive
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - After initial losses, the shares of CTS Eventim turned positive on Thursday. After falling minus 5.3 percent shortly after the start of Xetra trading and hitting a nine-week low, they recently gained 0.6 percent to 58.70 euros.      For the first time in a first half-year, CTS Eventim's consolidated sales climbed to more than one billion euros. Adjusted earnings (Ebitda) rose to 170.8 million euros. The company became more confident for the current full year, with earnings expected to grow moderately compared to the previous year.      Sales in the second quarter were unexpectedly strong, wrote analyst Thomas Maul of DZ Bank. He added that the live entertainment segment was the main contributor to this, although it was not very profitable. Looking ahead, the expert noted that presales for Taylor Swift's "The Eras Tour" got off to a very successful start in July. The tour, he said, has the potential to be a "mega-seller."      From an investor's point of view, the current Borsen year has been lukewarm so far. The share is virtually treading water. In May and June, there were strong price gains, with the share price rising by up to 20 percent by June 9. But then the share price began to fall sharply. The trigger was a program by TV satirist Jan Bohmermann, in which he took issue with the market position and fee policy of the event marketer and ticket retailer, among other things./bek/ngu/jha/

title: Air Liquide: share price rises, Berenberg upgrades to buy
full_text: Air Liquide was the second-biggest riser on the CAC 40 index on the Paris Bourse this Thursday, after Berenberg upgraded its recommendation on the stock to 'buy'.Shortly before 10.30 a.m., the French industrial gases specialist's share price climbed 1.6%, just behind Capgemini (+1.9%), which is benefiting from the craze for technology stocks following the good results published by Nvidia.This morning, Berenberg raised its recommendation on Air Liquide to 'buy' from 'hold', with a price target raised from €165 to €178.In its research note, the German bank praises the industrial group's 'better-than-expected' operational discipline.The reason why we held a neutral opinion on Air Liquide for some time was our concern about possible over-investment in the highly fragmented hydrogen and ammonia segment", says the intermediary.Berenberg explains that it feared that this strategy would lead the group to move away from its traditional business model based on take-or-pay contracts, so characteristic of the sector.On the contrary, the last few quarters have shown that the company is paying close attention to its investment policy, despite a stronger balance sheet that could encourage it to increase spending", he points out.On the stock market, Air Liquide shares are now up over 24% since the start of the year, making them one of the strongest annual gains in the CAC 40 index, alongside STM, Hermès, Saint-Gobain, Stellantis and Safran.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. All rights reserved.

title: Deutsche Bank starts SMA Solar with 'Hold' - Target 85 euros
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - Deutsche Bank Research has added SMA Solar to its rating with a "hold" rating and a target price of 85 euros. "Powered by sunny solutions," analyst Mengxian Sun headlined in a research report available Thursday. She praised the solar supplier given its positioning for long-term structural growth in renewables, its repositioning as an integrated solution provider for energy management and its highly predictable financials in the next six to 12 months. However, he said, these are factors that are unlikely to pull the market out of its rut. Moreover, demand appears to be normalizing in the coming quarters. title: Metzler optimistic for SAP's cloud business - 'Buy'.
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - Bankhaus Metzler sees great growth potential for SAP 's cloud activities. A new phase of the cloud era is beginning for the software manufacturer, analyst Oliver Frey wrote in a study presented on Tuesday. He included the software group's stock in his rating with a "buy" rating and a price target of 148 (current price: 128.06) euros.      The decision to move into the subscription-based, online rental software (cloud) business and the associated investments are crucial for SAP's future competitiveness, Frey believes. The measures taken are increasingly having an impact and are reflected in the updated ambitions for 2025.      Momentum is clearly on the side of the cloud, he said. Only a small double-digit number of customers still choose to buy software, while hundreds of customers had moved to the cloud in the first quarter of 2023. Cloud activities should not only be the dominant source of revenue for SAP this year, but also the main driver of double-digit percentage growth in operating profit, the expert predicts.      Rated "Buy," Bankhaus Metzler expects the company's share price to rise over the next 12 months./edh/tih/jha/  Analyzing institute Metzler Capital Markets.      Publication of the original study: 22.08.2023 / 07:55 / CEST First disclosure of the original study: 22.08.2023 / 07:55 / CEST

title: TECHNIP ENERGIES :  Morgan Stanley resumes 'Overweight' coverage
full_text: Morgan Stanley reinstated its coverage of Technip Energies on Monday, with an 'overweight' recommendation and a new price target of 26.2 euros, indicating a potential upside of 25%.In a sector note, the broker believes that the French group's strategy of focusing on the highest-margin contracts that are easiest to monetize is beginning to bear fruit.While the stock is now trading in line with its peers, compared with a 10% discount at the end of 2022, the broker points out that it still has potential, given the group's attractive positioning in the sought-after themes of energy transition, from carbon capture to hydrogen production.Morgan Stanley ranks Technip Energies as its top pick in the energy services sector, ahead of Italy's Saipem and Norway's Subsea 7.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Technip Energies: share price rises, Morgan Stanley sees potential
full_text: On Monday, Technip Energies shares posted the biggest rise in the SBF 120 index, with Morgan Stanley judging that the share's upside potential has not yet been exhausted.At 1:45 pm, the share price had climbed 4.1%, while the SBF 120 index had advanced 1.2%, bringing its gains since the start of the year to over 45%.Morgan Stanley resumed coverage of the stock on Monday, with an 'overweight' recommendation and a new target price of 26.2 euros, pointing to potential upside of 25%.In a sector note, the broker believes that the French group's strategy of focusing on the highest-margin contracts that are easiest to monetize is beginning to bear fruit.While the stock is now trading in line with its peers, compared with a 10% discount at the end of 2022, the broker points out that it still has potential, given the group's attractive positioning in the sought-after themes of energy transition, from carbon capture to hydrogen production.Morgan Stanley has named Technip Energies its "top pick" ahead of Italy's Saipem and Norway's Subsea 7 in the energy services sector.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. All rights reserved.

title: VALLOUREC :  Jefferies raises its price target
full_text: On Thursday, Jefferies reiterated its Buy recommendation on Vallourec, with a new target price of 17 euros, up from 16 euros.In a research note issued following the publication of the French group's second-quarter results, the broker indicates that it has revised upwards its Ebitda forecast for 2023 and reduced its net debt target.While it acknowledges that the difficulties encountered by the Pau Branco iron mine are not good news, the broker says it is pleased with the recent robustness of its tube prices.Jefferies also praises the solid performance of its offshore and international divisions, which has enabled the Group to offset the normalization of oil tubular product prices in the United States.The next catalyst, according to Jefferies, will be the company's investor day on September 12.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Bernstein raises target for Symrise to 107 euros - 'Market-Perform'.
full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX Broker) - U.S.-based analyst firm Bernstein Research raised its price target on Symrise to 107 euros from 102 euros and left its rating at "market perform." Analyst Gunther Zechmann shed light on the company's organic growth in Thursday's industry report on global chemical companies focused on the consumer goods sector. In the second quarter, declining sales volumes had weighed, although Symrise had again been the growth leader. For the fourth quarter, there are general signs of a slight upturn in sales volumes. full_text: ZURICH (dpa-AFX Broker) - Major Swiss bank UBS downgraded Carl Zeiss Meditec from "buy" to "neutral" and lowered its price target from 148 to 101 euros. The medical technology company has had to overcome external and internal issues in fiscal 2022/23, which have led to underperformance of the share price so far this year, analyst Graham Doyle wrote in a research note available Thursday. title: MAUREL & PROM :  Oddo BHF confirms its recommendation on the share
full_text: Oddo BHF confirms its neutral rating on Maurel & Prom (M&P) shares, with an unchanged target price of 3.5 euros. Last night, M&P announced that it had signed a share purchase agreement for the acquisition of Assala from Carlyle International Energy Partners.  Assala's assets are located in Gabon, an area that M&P knows very well, and this combination should enable significant operational and financial optimizations", estimates Oddo BHF. The transaction is expected to close between the fourth quarter of 2023 and the first quarter of 2024.The Transaction consideration paid to the seller by M&P at closing amounts to $730 million, subject to customary closing adjustments. Oddo BHF states that this transaction involves "little risk from an operational point of view", as M&P knows the area very well. Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: DANONE :  Bernstein downgrades to 'underperform
full_text: On Tuesday, Bernstein downgraded its opinion on Danone shares from 'in line with market performance' to 'underperform', with a price target lowered from 55 to 50 euros.In a wide-ranging study of the European food and consumer goods sectors, the analysts explain that Danone, along with Henkel, Reckitt and Unilever, are among the market players currently 'least well positioned for future success'.We are well aware that many investors appreciate Danone's turnaround because of the good choices the CEO seems to be making", stresses the research firm."We share this view, but we have no evidence yet that this strategy is working, and that it will significantly improve future growth, brand strength and price control", concludes Bernstein.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: L'ORÉAL :  Bernstein raises its opinion, target raised
full_text: On Tuesday, Bernstein raised its opinion on L'Oréal from 'in line with market performance' to 'outperform', with a target price raised from 425 to 440 euros.In a wide-ranging study of the European food and consumer goods sectors, Bernstein's analysts consider the French cosmetics giant, along with Lindt, to be among the best positioned players to face the challenges ahead.In particular, they highlight the group's presence in buoyant segments, the strength of its brands and its limited - or even non-existent - exposure to currency effects.The research firm also hails growth that is tending to diversify, with the hexagonal group able to allocate its advertising and promotional expenditure to the regions, products and ranges showing the most potential, a quality that Bernstein believes is currently poorly assessed by the market.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: THALES :  Barclays lowers its target price
full_text: On Friday, Barclays reiterated its 'weighted in line' recommendation on Thales, while lowering its target price for the stock from €154 to €148.In a research note, the research firm justifies its decision by the series of acquisitions recently completed by the French group, from Tesserent (cybersecurity) to AeroComms (cockpit communications systems).Barclays estimates that this buying frenzy will result in an increase in the company's net debt, from 781 million euros in June 2023 to 1.8 billion euros by the end of 2024.While appreciating the strategic significance of the Imperva acquisition, which will enable the company to strengthen its expertise in civil cybersecurity, the intermediary also notes that the operation will be costly.Pending finalization of the transaction, scheduled for early 2024, it is the Digital Identity and Security (DIS) branch that should determine Thales's performance in 2023, Barclays points out, although it cites 'limited visibility' at this stage on the division's dynamism.From a more general point of view, the analyst acknowledges that the Group is 'defensively positioned', but that its nature is also more cyclical than that of its peers.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: SWISSQUOTE GROUP HOLDING  :  H1-23: NII tailwinds persist; 2023 guidance upgraded
full_text:
H1-23: NII tailwinds persist; 2023 guidance upgraded EARNINGS/SALES RELEASESSwissquote realized a good H1-23, continuing to reap the benefits of higher rates on its liquidity and investment portfolio, more than offsetting the decline observed in transaction volumes linked to fading market volatility and an uncertain economic environment. The management upgraded both its 2023 revenue and pre-tax profit guidance on the back of the higher margins anticipated on its client assets. In our view the bank looks well positioned to contend with any challenges ahead. FACTOperating income: CHF265m (+32% yoy, 4% above our estimates and 2% above consensus). 
• Net fee and commission income: CHF81m (-19% yoy).
• Net interest income (NII): CHF103m vs CHF15m in H1-22. 
• Net trading income: CHF81m (-4% yoy). 
Opex: CHF138m (+30% yoy and 5% above our estimates). 
Net result from JV: CHF2.3m loss (vs CHF2.9m loss in H1-22). 
Pre-tax result: CHF125m (+38% yoy, 3% above our estimates and 9% below the consensus). Pre-tax profit margin at 47% vs 45% in H1-22. This was above the management’s 2023 target (46.5%). 
Client assets reached CHF56.9bn (vs CHF52.2bn in FY-22). The number of client accounts rose by 6.4% yoy to 555k accounts. 
Net new money: CHF3bn vs CHF2.7bn in H2-22 and CHF5bn in H1-22. 
The management upgraded both its revenue and pre-tax result targets for 2023 on the back of an upgraded outlook on NII, forecasting CHF530m of revenue (vs CHF495m) and a CHF250m pre-tax result (vs CHF230m) thus leading to a 47% pre-tax profit margin.
Management 2025 targets were kept unchanged: a CHF750m revenue, a CHF350m pretax result (47.5% pretax margin) and CHF7bn net new money per year. ANALYSISSwissquote realized a good H1-23, continuing to reap the benefits of higher rates on its liquidity and investment portfolio, more than offsetting the decline observed in transaction volumes linked to fading market volatility and an uncertain economic environment. The management upgraded both its 2023 revenue and pre-tax profit guidance on the back of the higher margins anticipated on its client assets thanks to the elevated interest rate levels foreseen. All the 2025 targets were maintained. The group continues to look fit for any coming environment, with non-transaction revenue coming notably from higher interest margins and a positive impact from market volatility on fee and trading income acting as mutual hedges. 
Revenue came in above the guidance with much of the growth coming from the very high NII. This was mainly due to the continued general increase in interest rates observed across all major currencies (CHF, USD, EUR) but also from the continued rise in client cash deposits (CHF9.4bn vs CHF9.2bn at the end of 2022) coming from the combination of new money and continued customer cautiousness. Another tailwind on NII came from the fact that the group invested a larger part of these deposits in loans and investment securities, anticipating the maturities of its portfolio, thus increasing the yield generated. Part of the rationale for this came from the fact that the management expected policy rates hikes to be close to their highs in developed economies, rendering duration more attractive than in 2022. The management expects higher interest rates to continue to draw NII higher in 2023, leading to a considerable increase in the margin on assets forecasted (94bp vs 87bp guided in 2022, with higher interest margin on deposits being solely responsible for the rise in margins). 
The management was confident in its interest margin outlook which should more than compensate for the low-volatility recorded in the market over H1-23 as well as the high uncertainty surrounding the economic outlook, which led to continued cautiousness in client positioning. Should volatility return in H2-23 and 2024, transaction volume will likely benefit from this shift in the market environment which could play out in favour of Swissquote’s fee income generation and the group achieving its 2025 revenue target. Cryptos are another source of potential tailwinds which could emerge in the coming environment, with interest returning to this market, as the industry experiences short but abrupt cycles and as the current “crypto winter” is about to celebrate its two-year anniversary at the end of the year. On the other hand, a shadow overhanging the group’s NII tailwind which has so far not shown its presence is a possible increase in the pass-through rate, the proportion of policy rate hikes returned to depositors as remuneration on the cash held in their accounts, which could occur as competitive pressure emerges and a fight for deposits begins among banks and other financial institutions. 
Opex growth, although quite substantial, was due largely to the rise in staff headcount (+7% yoy), higher variable remuneration (CHF9.7m vs CHF3.1m for H1-22), higher marketing expenses (+21% yoy) and investments in growth. The management indicated that the group remained committed to investing in technology as it remains a critical element in improving services for customers and attracting new business and fresh money, thus sticking to future pre-tax margin improvement instead of the current pre-tax margin maximization.
All in all, the H1 was an illustration of how Swissquote’s business model remains one of economies-of-scale, leaving the online bank and broker well positioned to contend with the potentially uncertain coming market environment. IMPACTThe results were slightly above our estimates. Given the upgraded 2023 guidance, we may review upward our forecasts.

title: JPMorgan leaves Salzgitter at 'Underweight' - Target 23.30 euros
full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX Broker) - U.S. bank JPMorgan left its rating on Salzgitter AG at "underweight" with a price target of 23.30 euros after second-quarter figures. The pre-tax profit is in line with the already known key data, analyst Moses Ola wrote in a study published on Friday. The development of cash flow has not been known so far. This at least exceeded his estimate. However, the analyst remains negative on the stock, as the steelmaker is relatively heavily dependent on spot steel prices and could therefore feel the impact of falling prices in the short term. full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its Outperform rating on Coface shares, with an unchanged target price of 14.5 euros. Last night, Coface reported Q2 revenues of €485 million (+8.7% on a reported basis), slightly ahead of expectations (€481 million). "Following the publication of its good NI, we are raising our 2023 NI forecast by around 5% to 237 ME, given the good momentum in terms of underwriting results, and we are raising our 2024 NI forecast by 3% to 217 ME assuming a gradual further normalization of claims experience", says the analyst. title: UBS downgrades MTU to 'Neutral' and target to 230 euros
full_text: ZURICH (dpa-AFX) - Major Swiss bank UBS has downgraded MTU from "buy" to "neutral" and lowered its price target from 270 to 230 euros. Although the engine manufacturer's stock has already priced in recent headwinds from metal quality issues, analyst Kseniia Maslova still sees risks. The new investment vote mainly reflects her reduced long-term growth and margin forecasts, she wrote in a research report available Thursday./edh/ajx/ck      Original study publication date: 08/10/2023 / 00:18 / GMT  First disclosure of original study: 10.08.2023 / 00:18 / GMT----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: ThyssenKrupp end losing streak for now
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - After a dry spell that began in mid-July, thyssenkrupp shares moved back into forward gear on Thursday. They rose by 3.7 percent to 6.90 euros after the figures for the second quarter. Before that, they had lost more than eleven percent from their recent high four weeks ago. The 200-day line currently at 6.60 euros had held as support on Tuesday.      Investors were therefore cautious in the quarterly report of the industrial group. This was well received by Moses Ola from JPMorgan. Both from the perspective of the individual divisions and in terms of cash flow, the figures were strong. The operating profit of the steel business in Europe exceeded market expectations by almost a fifth.      Free cash flow, meanwhile, was more than twice as high as expected. It had benefited from a working capital release of almost 300 million euros, the expert said./bek/zb----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: SANOFI  :  AlphaValue renews its buy recommendation
full_text: On Wednesday, AlphaValue renewed its Buy recommendation on Sanofi, with a price target of 132 euros corresponding to a potential upside of 38%.At a time when other stocks in the sector such as Novo Nordisk and Eli Lilly are focusing investors' attention, the research consultancy believes that it is also time to take a look at the French pharmaceutical giant, whose 'silent performance' it praises.Over the past five years, Sanofi has seen both its profitability and its stock market valuation rise at a steady pace, despite the difficulties the laboratory has had to face, it points out.As for its prospects, not only does its flagship drug Dupixent still offer significant growth potential, but the group also has promising projects in other areas, notes AlphaValue.With a current P/E of 15x compared with a historical average of 20x over the 2013-2022 period, the stock is currently trading at a discounted valuation, which tells the research firm that the stock represents an attractive investment opportunity.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: AXA :  Berenberg raises its price target
full_text: Berenberg announced on Wednesday that it had raised its price target for AXA from 33 to 33.5 euros, while renewing its buy recommendation on the stock.In a note issued this morning, the analyst recalls that the French insurance giant recently expressed confidence in its ability to achieve underlying earnings in excess of 7.5 billion euros this year."Looking at the first-half accounts, and assuming that AXA will manage to generate operating capital in line with its target of 25% to 30%, in line with its Solvency II model, we believe this implies the prospect of earnings of 7.8 billion euros in 2023, 100 million more than our forecast of 7.7 billion," explains the financial intermediary.Berenberg says it has accordingly raised its operating profit estimate for the current year by 100 million, and its forecasts for the coming years by the same amount.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. The auto supplier's second-quarter report was solid and met and partly exceeded its estimates, analyst Peter Rothenaicher wrote in a first reaction on Tuesday. There is now some "light on the horizon" again. The figures were characterized by moderate organic growth. In addition, the annual targets were confirmed./ck/ajx      Publication of the original study: 08.08.2023 / 08:36 / CEST  First disclosure of original study: Date not stated in study / Time not stated in study / Time zone not stated in study----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: Barclays leaves Fraport at 'Overweight' - Target 62 euros
full_text: LONDON (dpa-AFX) - British investment bank Barclays left its rating for Fraport at "Overweight" with a price target of 62 euros after figures. The second quarter was slightly below consensus forecasts in terms of operating profit (Ebitda) and slightly above consensus forecasts in terms of net profit, analyst Andrew Lobbenberg wrote in a research note published on Tuesday. He also pointed to the raised full-year targets at the upper end of the forecast ranges. He expects questions on the conference call to include questions about costs, the 2024 rate filing and revenue trends./ck/ajx      Original study publication date: 08/08/2023 / 06:15 / GMT  First disclosure of the original study: 08.08.2023 / 06:16 / GMT----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: Metzler upgrades FMC to 'Buy' - Target raised to 54 euros
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - Bankhaus Metzler upgraded Fresenius Medical Care (FMC) from "hold" to "buy" and raised its price target from 41 to 54 euros. title: Ipsen: share price rises, two analysts optimistic
full_text: Ipsen shares rose sharply on the Paris Bourse on Tuesday, posting the second biggest gain on the SBF 120 index, buoyed by optimistic comments from Deutsche Bank and AlphaValue.At 11:15 a.m., the French pharmaceutical company's shares were up 2.6%, while the SBF 120 was down 0.6% at the same time.In a note released this morning, Deutsche Bank said it had raised its target price for the stock from €100 to €124, citing "an improving business case"."The half-year results confirmed that the company is transitioning to a multi-launch phase focused on commercial execution, far from the concerns currently surrounding Somatuline", explains the research firm.Deutsche Bank maintains its 'hold' recommendation on the stock.AlphaValue also describes the company as an 'attractive small pharma stock''After a promising end to the 2022 financial year, followed by a vigorous first-half performance, we are raising our price target by 23%, thanks to a robust pipeline combined with encouraging clinical results in recent months, favorable trials expected in the coming months and a solid balance sheet', it concludes.His target has thus been raised to 168 euros from 137 euros previously, with a recommendation raised to 'buy' from 'accumulate'.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. All rights reserved.

title: ATOS  :  AlphaValue lowers its target price
full_text: AlphaValue announced Monday that it has lowered its price target for Atos to 10.2 euros from 21.1 euros, while renewing its buy recommendation on the stock.In a research note, the research firm justifies its decision by the deterioration in the technology group's cash flow and the risk of dilution associated with the proposed 900 million euro capital increase.While it considers the sale of Tech Foundations to be "good news", as is its announced purchase price of two billion euros, the Paris-based consultancy believes that this fund-raising, as well as the project to eliminate around one billion euros of working capital requirements, represent far less positive surprises.With regard to Eviden, the cybersecurity subsidiary that is to be spun off, AlphaValue points out that the entity will have net debt of 1.9 billion euros, or 3.9 times its Ebitda, a ratio that should be reduced to 2x by 2025 on the basis of a turnaround scenario that the analyst deems "ambitious" in what he sees as an "unstable" period.Atos is clearly penalized by a loss of confidence following all the disappointments of recent years", he concludes. There is nothing to look forward to until the capital increase is launched".Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: CRÉDIT AGRICOLE :  price target raised by Oddo BHF

title: Berenberg upgrades K+S to 'Buy' - Target raised to 22 euros
full_text: HAMBURG (dpa-AFX) - Private bank Berenberg upgraded K+S to "buy" from "hold" and raised its price target to 22.00 euros from 16.70 euros. title: Siemens Energy falls - Liberation blow is a long time coming
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - Siemens Energy shareholders continue to have nothing to smile about: On Monday, the papers fell after quarterly figures and outlook in pre-borsday trading on Tradegate by 5.2 percent at the Xetra close to 14.74 euros.      Although traders praised the fact that the burdens of the wind power subsidiary Gamesa were now finally quantified, the outlook of the energy technology group was sobering. The losses in Gamesa's wind business have counteracted everything positive, wrote analyst Akash Gupta of JPMorgan.      At the end of June, the Dax-listed shares had lost 37 percent of their market capitalization in just one day, making them one of the biggest daily losers in the German benchmark index.       The reason was the problems at Gamesa, which is why the group had to withdraw its forecasts. At 13.75 euros, the shares had marked the lowest price since November 2022. They have hardly recovered since then./ajx/zb----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: Nexans: down slightly, broker reduces target
full_text: Nexans is down nearly 0.6% in Paris, as Oddo BHF announced this morning that it was maintaining its 'neutral' rating on the stock, with a price target reduced from 90 to 88 euros.The analyst firm reports that management remains confident but more cautious for the second half of the year.The new EBITDA guidance (€610/650m vs. €570/630m) reflects this caution," says Oddo BHF, which estimates that, based on the upper end of the range, H2 EBITDA would be €296m, i.e. stable vs. H2 2022. The lower end of the range would translate into a decline of almost 12% vs. H2 2022.'Against this backdrop, we have adjusted our 2023 EBITDA estimate by +3% to ME 630 (+5% YoY, mid-range guidance, css ME 595), i.e. a 9.5% margin (+60bp), of which 10.7% in H1 and 8.3% in H2', says the analyst. title: ERAMET  :  AlphaValue recommends 'light'.
full_text: On Thursday, AlphaValue cut its recommendation on Eramet shares from "buy" to "reduce", with a price target reduced from 116 to 76.2 euros.In a research note, the research firm considers that the situation has become "more complicated" on all the mining and metallurgical group's markets.According to the research firm, the only light at the end of the tunnel is the prospect of an upturn in nickel production at the Weda Bay site, in which Eramet holds a 38.7% stake.For AlphaValue, this promise is a slight improvement on a scenario that it considers 'rather depressing', leading it to advise investors to be patient in the face of a stock market dynamic that it expects to remain unfavorable until at least the end of the year.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: ATOS :  recommendation and target 'under review' at Invest Securities
full_text: Invest Securities announces that its recommendation and price target for Atos shares are now 'under review'.  Indeed, in view of "massive uncertainty over dilution", the analyst considers that he is currently unable to define a price target. Previously, the broker had positioned itself as 'buy', with a target of 18 euros.  In retrospect, we can better understand the deterioration in results and FCF in the 1st half of the year, as Atos wanted to put a stop to the situation before selling Tech Foundations to D. Kretinsky", says the broker. While the sale price of Tech Foundations (EV of E2bn) is good news, 'the entity that will remain listed will be heavily indebted, which is why Atos has finally announced a capital increase of E900m, contrary to the commitment made by management in June 2022', stresses the research firm. Invest Securities also points out that, given that 80% of this capital increase will take place at a price that is not yet fixed, the risk of massive dilution is high, and will increase as the share price falls.As a reminder, the share price fell by some 16% yesterday. full_text: LONDON (dpa-AFX Broker) - U.K.-based investment bank Barclays downgraded Telefonica Deutschland to "Equal Weight" from "Overweight" and cut its price target to 2.50 euros from 3.60 euros. title: BONDUELLE :  Oddo BHF confirms its recommendation on the stock
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its 'neutral' rating on Bonduelle shares, with an unchanged target price of 13 euros. Last night, Bonduelle reported Q4 sales in line with expectations, at 590.7 ME (586 MEe), up 5.2% including 1.2% forex.  Organic growth came to 4%, close to our expectations of 4.2%e, implying annual growth for 2022/23 of 5%, in line with our guidance", emphasized the analyst. Overall for the year, sales rose by 9.2% to ME 2,406.2, and Bonduelle confirmed its guidance of an operating margin before non-recurring items of close to 2.5%, despite an inflationary context and a downturn in food consumption since the third quarter. Against this background, Oddo BHF considers this publication to be "fairly in line" with its expectations and those of the consensus. We have no reason to change our forecasts at this stage. Bonduelle's operating profitability will most probably be driven by the European zone', concludes the research firm. Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. full_text: On Wednesday, Portzamparc announced that it had added Eramet to its 'High Five' list of small and mid-cap stocks specially recommended for purchase by its analysts.The research consultancy says it expects the mining and metallurgy group's performance to improve in the second half of the year, while highlighting its 'quality assets'.Portzamparc, which is maintaining its 'buy' recommendation, says it has a price target of 192 euros, showing a potential upside of 162%.It also cites an "undemanding" valuation, with an Enterprise Value/Ebitda ratio of 3.8x, compared with a five-year average of 6.4x and a level of 5.3x among its comparables.On Wednesday, Portzamparc added Delta Plus, Eramet and Ipsos to its list of recommended "High Five" stocks, while removing Esker, Infotel and Focus Entertainment.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: ATOS :  price target lowered by Oddo BHF
full_text: Oddo BHF has reiterated its 'underperform' rating on Atos, with a price target reduced from 10.5 to 7.5 euros, believing that the stock 'will inevitably remain under pressure' following the announcement of the proposed sale of Tech Foundations (TFCo).On paper, this transaction raised hopes for Atos shareholders, but the fact that the Group will have to finance TFCo's working capital largely clouds the picture", says the analyst in charge of the file.TFCo's sale price is below market expectations, and Eviden is left with a high level of net debt, forcing it to carry out a massive and highly dilutive capital increase, as its equity is crushed in the process", he stresses.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Cancom continues to slide - analysts take a negative view of figures
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - Cancom shares continued their steep slide on Wednesday. They lost a further 7.2 percent to 23.82 euros in the morning. Already on the previous day, the quarterly report and a forecast reduction had been negatively received by the market.      With the slide in the share price on Wednesday, the IT service provider was one of the biggest losers in the small cap index SDax. In addition, the shares retreated even further from the 21-day line, which is considered a gauge of short-term share price performance, to a low since October 2022.      Several analysts commented negatively on the quarterly report and lowered their price targets. Lars Vom-Cleff of Deutsche Bank called the figures another bose surprise, while Andreas Wolf of Warburg Research focused on the lowered annual targets as a further blow to investor confidence./gl/jha/

title: KLÉPIERRE :  Oddo BHF raises its target slightly
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its 'outperform' rating on Klépierre shares, with a target price raised slightly from 26 to 26.5 euros. The analyst reports that last night, Klépierre published "very good results in line with its peers", with operating indicators stabilizing at high levels, but also a CFNC/share at 1.21 E (+7.4% yoy) vs. 1.20 E and particularly resilient asset values (-1.4% over 6M).Retail sales rose by 8% in the 1st half, and organic growth in net rental income on a like-for-like basis reached 7.3%.As a result, Klépierre is raising its 2023 guidance and now expects a 2023 CFNC/share at 'at least 2.40 E' vs. 2.35 E previously, up 7% on the adjusted 2022 CFNC/share of 2.24 E due to a better-than-expected operating performance. Oddo BHF highlights 'a very solid publication from Klépierre, which here confirms its status as a benchmark player among retail property companies'. Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: KLÉPIERRE :  Invest Securities raises its target
full_text: Invest Securities reiterates its 'buy' recommendation on Klépierre, with a price target raised from 25.1 to 26.2 euros, judging in particular that 'growth prospects are limited, but the level of the dividend is guaranteed in the medium term'.  Klépierre has published very good operating data, which has led it to revise its guidance for CFNC 2023 very slightly to 2.40 euros per share", emphasized the analyst the day after the property company's half-yearly publication.We are just noting signs of maturity in the French and Northern European centers, and financial communications are strangely becoming less rich", he continues, adding that "valuation declines, which are set to continue, are slight".Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Scor: ends the day in the green, broker raises target
full_text: The stock ended the session with a gain of nearly 1%, benefiting from a positive analysis by Deutsche Bank. The analyst announced on Tuesday that he had raised his target price for Scor shares from 30 to 34 euros, believing that the French reinsurer now has the wind in its sails.Although the stock has posted a total return (including dividend) of almost 35% this year, compared with a 10% gain for the STOXX Europe 600 Insurance sector index, it is only trading at around 5.5 times earnings to 2025, notes the analyst, who refers to a "significant" discount to the PERs on which its comparables trade, ranging from eight to 11x.For the intermediary, however, it is becoming "increasingly clear that the Group is taking the right steps, and that its initiatives should soon bear fruit".Deutsche Bank thus perceives an upside potential of more than 50% for the stock, which it continues to recommend as a Buy and which it has made one of its favorite stocks within the sector.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. All rights reserved.

title: KERING :  Stifel remains Buy, lowers its target
full_text: While maintaining its 'buy' recommendation on Kering, Stifel has lowered its target price to 625 euros, following a reduction of its 2023-24 EBIT projections by 3% for the luxury group.The broker justifies this reduction by lower growth for Gucci and YSL, lower margin assumptions for Gucci and other brands, as well as negative currency effects.However, it sees potential for share price appreciation 'if the market starts to anticipate improved sales momentum for Gucci in 2024, following significant management changes and the new creative vision to be unveiled in September'.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: EURONEXT :  BofA raises its price target
full_text: On Tuesday, Bank of America raised its price target for Euronext from €80 to €83, while renewing its buy recommendation on the stock market operator's shares.In a research note, the financial intermediary cites "reassuring" second-quarter results, the accretive impact of its share buyback program, and the low stock market valuation.BofA also expects potentially positive surprises in terms of the Group's operating performance, thanks to cost reductions and higher-than-expected synergies from its merger with Borsa Italiana.With regard to the proposed reform of the financial markets, in particular the introduction of a consolidated market data system, the analyst says he does not expect any 'significant' impact at this stage, given investors' preference for real-time quotes.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: LEGRAND :  Oddo BHF confirms its recommendation on the stock
full_text: Oddo BHF confirms its neutral rating on Legrand shares, with an unchanged target price of 88 euros. Yesterday morning, Legrand published H1 results slightly above expectations (5% in adjusted EBIT). In Q2, Legrand surprised by low volumes but also by strong margins, according to the analysts. Organic sales growth in Q2 was only 2% (consensus 3.6%). In H1, volumes were down 2.7%, while prices were up 7.3%. EBITA margin rose by 170 bp to 22.2%, supported by the wide gap between price increases and inflation in raw materials and components (+0.3% in H1 for the latter).  Our EPS for 2023 and 2024 are revised upwards by 1.6% on average. We include the latest acquisition (Teknica, 45 ME, Chile, UPS for datacenters). We now forecast organic sales growth of 3.3% (including -1.5% in volumes) and an adjusted EBIT margin of 20.1% for 2023', stresses the analyst. Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: CRÉDIT AGRICOLE :  Oddo BHF reiterates its recommendation
full_text: Crédit Agricole SA will publish its results for Q2 2023 on August 4. Oddo BHF expects revenues of 5,891 ME, down 6.9% on a very high base in Q2 2022, with very strong revenues in Wholesale Banking. ' Our forecast is close to consensus (5,911 ME) '. ' By business line, we forecast: 1/ a 2.0% increase in asset gathering revenues, 2/ a 7.8% drop in revenues in French retail banking (LCL) 3/ a strong increase (+19.4%) in international retail banking revenues 4/ a 5.2% increase in revenues in specialized financial services; 5/ a 9.5% drop in revenues in Large Customers ' indicates Oddo BHF.' We expect costs to fall by 4.3%, leading us to forecast gross operating income of 2,579 ME (-10.1%), marginally above consensus (2,561 ME) ' says Oddo BHF.  Overall, we forecast RO of 2,093 ME (-21.5%) in Q2 2023, very slightly above consensus (2,064 ME, -22.6%). We expect NI of 1,428 ME (-27.7%), also slightly above consensus (1,391 ME, -29.6%)' adds the analyst firm. Oddo BHF reiterates its Outperform recommendation on the share, with a target price of E13.6.  The share's current valuation does not reflect the quality of the Group's business mix, and in particular its strong exposure to insurance and AM, which generate high profitability and retain attractive medium/long-term growth potential," explains the analyst.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: EURONEXT :  Deutsche Bank raises its target price
full_text: Deutsche Bank announced on Monday that it had raised its target price for Euronext shares from €69 to €75, following better-than-expected second-quarter results.In addition to the better-than-expected performance reported by the stock market operator over the past quarter, the research firm hails the launch of a 200 million euro share buyback program.This first in the group's history is a positive surprise, it stresses, likely to revitalize the share price and boost a valuation deemed "depressed".While he expects Euronext to possibly improve its cost forecasts by the end of the year, DB stresses that the group's financial performance is still struggling to inspire him, and that no real turnaround seems to be on the horizon.In view of the limited upside potential revealed by its 75 euro target, Deutsche Bank therefore prefers to remain 'hold' on the stock.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Hermès: still in the green on brokers' comments

title: CEMENTIR HOLDING  :  H1 23: positive price-cost spread
full_text:
H1 23: positive price-cost spreadEARNINGS/SALES RELEASESCementir Holding announced a good set of results, which were in line with our expectations. Despite a decline in volume, the company managed to keep revenue stable thanks to higher average selling prices, while improving its margins thanks to its hedging policy and a presence in niche markets. EBITDA, excluding one-off effects, increased by 34% and the margin increased by 5.6pp.FACT
Revenue: €840.7m (vs €831.6m in H1 22)
EBITDA: €200.5m (vs €143.8m in H1 22)
Net profit: €90.3m (vs €66.6m in H1 22)
Outlook upgraded: EBITDA now around €365m (previously €335-345m)ANALYSISCementir Holding has reported a good set of H1 results, with a significant increase in revenue and EBITDA. Despite a decrease in the volumes of cement (-5.5%), RMC (-11.3%) and aggregates (-15.3%), the company managed to achieve a 1.1% increase in revenue and a 39.5% increase in EBITDA due to its successful management of price over costs. 
The higher EBITDA was seen in all markets, allowing the company to reach a margin of 23.9%, 6.6pp higher than in the previous year thanks to strong pricing as well as the company’s careful management of energy costs, supported by a strong hedging policy. It is worth noting that EBITDA includes €7.5m of capital gains; excluding this one-off, the margin stands at 22.9%, 5.6pp higher than in the previous year. 
While energy costs have reached their peak in the last year, they have now stabilised at a level that is still higher than the average of previous years. Consequently, we anticipate that prices will follow the same trend in the coming quarter and stabilise. However, it is important to note that inflation might cause labour and financial costs to continue to rise this year.
Performance by division
In the Nordic and Baltic regions, which contributed 40% of the group’s EBITDA, sales experienced a 5.7% decrease due to declining volumes in both domestic and export markets. However, there are signs of stabilisation in the volume decline. The negative trend in these regions can be attributed to high inflation and increased interest rates, which have impacted the residential sector and investments in public works. Despite these challenges, there is a notable development with the construction of an underwater tunnel connecting Denmark to Germany, which managed to offset partially the volume decline in Denmark. As a result, Denmark saw a 4.7% increase in revenue and a significant 53.7% rise in EBITDA. On the other hand, Norway and Sweden were more severely affected, experiencing a 22% drop in revenue and a substantial 64% decline in EBITDA year on year. Nevertheless, the margin still increased by 8.3pp.
The Belgium and France segment showed a strong performance, with a 12% increase in revenue and an 18% increase in EBITDA, despite a double-digit volume decline. This was mainly due to successful price increases that offset the volume decline, and the EBITDA margin also saw a significant increase of 120bp, thanks to the efficient management of energy costs.
In North America, the US market encountered a 14% decrease in volume in Texas and California, mainly caused by competitive pressure from imports. As a result, despite implementing price increases and benefiting from a positive FX impact of 1.1%, revenue experienced a decline of 1.1%. Additionally, EBITDA also suffered, dropping by 18% due to higher operating costs, leading to a significant decrease of 320bp in the EBITDA margin.
In the Asia Pacific region, China experienced a 1.5% rise in revenue, attributed to the easing of COVID-19 restrictions in Q2. The substantial increase in volumes more than compensated for the decline observed in Q1. However, EBITDA, excluding one-time effects, decreased by 18% due to lower prices. On the other hand, in Malaysia, revenue remained stable despite a significant decrease in white cement exports, as it was offset by strong demand in the local market. Notably, EBITDA in Malaysia saw a remarkable increase of 43%, primarily driven by higher selling prices and reduced freight costs, partially balanced by increased production costs. Additionally, it is worth mentioning that both the Chinese Yuan (CNY) and Malaysian Ringgit (MYR) depreciated over the same period.
The company shifted focus from cement exports (down by 50%) to the more profitable domestic market. Antiseismic investment-driven projects increased demand, leading to a 38% revenue increase. EBITDA more than doubled to €34m as higher cement prices offset production costs. Excluding one-off effects, EBITDA reached €29m, with an 18% margin. Notably, the TRY devaluated by 32.7% compared to the Euro during the period.
In Egypt, revenue decreased by 5.1% primarily due to the negative impact of FX (74%). However, EBITDA increased by 44% due to the efficient management of production costs and an increase in selling prices, resulting in a 970bp increase in the margin.IMPACTThe company has raised its FY23 guidance and now anticipates EBITDA to be around €365m. Despite a robust quarter in a challenging environment, the management has adopted a cautious approach due to uncertainties related to the devaluation of the Turkish lira and the ongoing demand slowdown in the Nordics. Accounting for these factors, the estimates have been adjusted upwards, and the recommendation to buy the stock is reiterated.

title: ALTEN :  Invest Securities adjusts its price target
full_text: The analyst believes that after more than 8 consecutive quarters of organic growth (>+14%), the 2nd quarter of 2023 (+8.6%) marks a change in trend.  While the working day effect partly explains this slowdown (as well as an exceptional item in Singapore), it is above all the sign of a return to normal after a period of very high demand post COVID. The cautious message on margins, without being alarmist, could also make us tense up until the H1 23 results in mid-September", says Invest Securities.  As our estimates already incorporate a cautious scenario, we have no reason to change them (especially as Alten has announced 3 small acquisitions), but the consensus could reduce its expectations (-5% at NBI level)," adds the research firm. In view of this less favorable short-term momentum, Invest Securities reiterates its neutral opinion, with an adjusted target price of E142 (versus E146). Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: KERING :  Oddo BHF raises its price target
full_text: Kering has published sales of 10135 ME for the 1st half of 2023, up 2%, and group EBIT of 2739 ME, representing a margin of 27% (compared with 28.4% for the 2nd half of 2022).Following this announcement, Oddo BHF confirms its Neutral recommendation on the share and raises its target price to E526 (from E498). Oddo BHF was expecting sales of E10140 (organic growth in Q2 of +3%) and EBIT of E2724 (margin of 26.9%). The company's consensus was for sales of ME 10161 and ME 2716 (margin 26.7%) respectively.  The results are therefore very close to expectations, confirming that topline growth was still well below the sector average in Q2 (in our opinion +17%), and that profitability showed a visible but continuing decline", says Oddo BHF.  Retail sales trends by geography show a marked slowdown in Europe to +4% in Q2 after +15% in Q1, an even steeper decline in the Americas to -23% after -18% in Q1, a very good performance in Japan to +26% (Q1: +30%) helped by tourism, and finally a re-acceleration in Asia Pacific to +22% after +10% in Q1," stresses the analyst firm.  Outside Japan, these factors suggest a more marked slowdown for the Group in the US and Europe, and a recovery in Asia Pacific that is less visible than for the rest of the industry (two-year growth in Chinese spending in Q2 below 10%)'.The analyst believes that Gucci's Q2 growth is unchanged from Q1, and remains very weak at +1% (he was expecting +4%), while the H1 margin shows a slightly more pronounced decline to 35.3% from 36.5% in H1 2022 (he was targeting 35.8%).  The integration of more unfavorable exchange rates and greater caution on the Gucci top line for H2 2023 (Q3 at +3% vs. +7% previously, Q4 at +7% vs. +10%, i.e. FY growth at +3% vs. +6% previously) has led us to revise our annual sales forecasts very slightly downwards by -1%. The impact is more visible on EBIT (-2% 2023, -4% 2024 and -3% 2025) as we take into account the possibility of higher investments in Gucci's relaunch, leading to a normative margin in the transition period close to 35%' adds Oddo BHF.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Hauck Aufhäuser IB lowers target for Suess Microtec - 'Buy'
full_text: HAMBURG (dpa-AFX Broker) - Hauck Aufhäuser Investment Banking lowered its price target for Suess Microtec from 33 to 32 euros after capped annual targets, but left its rating at "Buy". The share price reaction on the previous day to the profit warning seems exaggerated, as the reason was the business development of Micro-Optics, analyst Jonah Emerson wrote in a study available on Friday. However, micro-optics is not part of the semiconductor equipment maker's core business, he added. Emerson, on the other hand, still considers Suess' short- and medium-term growth prospects and margin potential attractive, not least because of its involvement in artificial intelligence. However, he lowered his estimates to reflect the new targets./ck/zb      Publication of the original study: 28.07.2023 / 08:18 / CEST. title: SAFRAN :  price target raised by Oddo BHF
full_text: In the wake of its half-year results, Oddo BHF reiterates its 'outperform' rating on Safran and raises its target price from €151 to €171, after raising its estimates, integrating the SBB and updating its market assumptions.On this basis, the stock would trade on a 2025 PE of 21 times for a 2022-25 EPS TMVA of 34% and a cumulative FCF over the same period of 11.9 billion euros, versus 27% and 1.67 billion respectively for MTU', points out the analyst.Oddo BHF continues to prefer Safran in the engine-maker universe 'for its pricing power, the quality of its portfolio and the optionality opened up by the PW1100's after-sales difficulties in the short term, as well as the evolution of market shares in the medium term'.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Evotec sags after harsh warning
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - A harsh revenue and profit warning from Evotec weighed heavily on the share price in pre-market trading on Friday. The shares plunged 8.6 percent to 21.74 euros on Tradegate. In the pre-borsday low, the price loss even amounted to almost 12 percent.      The active ingredient researcher expects sales of only 750 to 790 million euros as a result of a hacker attack. Previously, 820 to 840 million euros had been on the cards for the current year. In terms of earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization (Ebitda), adjusted for special effects, management expects 60 to 80 million euros. Previously, Evotec had planned to increase this result to 115 to 130 million euros in the current year.      "That the annual targets would be cut was an open secret because of the cyberattack," a trader said. However, he said the extent of the cut in annual targets was "larger than feared."      Analyst Charles Weston of bank RBC noted that the market's expectation for Ebitda in the current year is now likely to be slashed by 42 percent, assuming the midpoint of Evotec's prospective range. In terms of sales, the corresponding reduction of the consensus estimate amounts to 8.5 percent.      The drop in the share price had recently become significantly higher: From the most recent low at the beginning of May, the share price had risen by around 55 percent and on Tuesday reached its highest level since August last year. Investors were therefore now also able to "cash in" and realize profits./bek/zb

title: VISIATIV :  Invest Securities downgrades its recommendation on the stock
full_text: Invest Securities has downgraded its recommendation on Visiativ shares from "buy" to "neutral", due to the recent rebound in the share price (+14pts over 3 months) and management's cautious message on short-term profitability. The analyst has also reduced his target price from €36 to €34.  While we are leaving our sales estimates unchanged, our earnings expectations have been significantly reduced for 2023-25, to take account of management's focus on growth and the migration of the model to subscription-based services", says Invest. The research firm points out that, while this does not call into question its positive medium/long-term opinion, the transition period could generate a certain amount of stress, especially as Visiativ remains a company with a high level of debt (95mE in liabilities for a capi of 150mE).Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Sartorius continues to rise - Chart and orders give hope
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - Sartorius preference shares continued their recent recovery on Thursday. With a gain of almost five percent to around 375 euros, they overcame the resistance at 360 euros. The shares had repeatedly failed at this level in mid-June and in recent days.      One observer said that last week's departure from the downward trend that began in early February had brightened the technical situation. From a fundamental perspective, sentiment had also improved, with the prospect of orders for the pharmaceutical and laboratory supplier rising again.       The next target on the way up is the so-called gap from April at 386.30 euros./bek/jha/zb

title: Warburg Research downgrades K+S to 'Hold' and targets 19 euros
full_text: HAMBURG (dpa-AFX Broker) - Analysts Warburg Research downgraded K+S to "hold" from "buy" and lowered its price target to 19 euros from 20 euros. Analyst Oliver Schwarz adjusted his estimates downward in a research note presented Thursday in response to a profit warning. "The outlook style is increasingly problematic," the expert wrote. He said the fertilizer group missed its second-quarter operating earnings (Ebitda) expectations by 50 million euros and lowered its full-year target from "at least 800 million euros" to a range of 600 million to 800 million euros. This implies at least a further decline of 50 million, while at the same time K+S is sending positive demand and price signals./ag/edh  Publication of the original study: 27.07.2023 / 08:15 / CEST First disclosure of the original study: Date not specified in study / Time not specified in study / CEST----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: AIRBUS :  Oddo BHF confirms its buy recommendation
full_text: The analyst believes that Airbus has published a solid 2nd quarter 2023 with Adjusted EBIT of 1,845 ME (+33.5%), 7% above consensus expectations on sales of 15.9 BnE, representing a margin of 11.6% (+82 bp). ' The difference with our estimates comes mainly from Airbus Commercial, which posted Adjusted EBIT of 1,676 ME (+9.8% > consensus) and a margin of 13.7% ' stresses the analyst firm.' The performance was driven in particular by i/ the delivery of 34 additional aircraft, ii/ a 3-cent improvement in the USD hedge (compared with our expectations of 5 cents), iii/ a 0.1 bnE reversal of provisions linked to compliance, despite a sharp acceleration in R&D (+15.5%) ' says Oddo BHF.Oddo confirms its Outperform recommendation on the stock, with a price target of 145 E.' In our view, visibility has improved for H2 2023, but RTX problems could marginally impact 2024 deliveries. Feedback from the inspection of the 200 engines in mid-September will be key to maintaining momentum," adds Oddo BHF.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: CARREFOUR :  Oddo BHF raises its price target
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its Outperform rating on Carrefour shares, with a price target raised from 19 to 20 euros.Carrefour reported last night an 8.2% rise in sales (incl. VAT) on a reported basis, of which 11.2% in LFL, to 45.4 billion euros. Sales in France showed a slight sequential deceleration to 7.3% in LFL (6.4%e), slightly above expectations, including 8.2% in Proximité (8.0%e), 6.6% in Hypermarkets (6.0%e) and 7.6% in Supermarkets (6.0%e).In addition, sales in Brazil came in at -3.2% in LFL, with a margin of 251 ME (270 MEe / CSS 244 ME), about which there had been a lot of questioning.  Following this publication, we are adjusting our ROI from 2,350 ME to 2,430 ME (France effect only)', says the analyst, who is raising his target price in view of an attractive valuation, lower than historical levels and peers, as well as good execution, particularly in France. title: Foncière Lyonnaise: in green, an analyst raises his recommendation
full_text: Foncière Lyonnaise gains more than 1% in Paris as Invest Securities raises its recommendation on the stock from 'sell' to 'neutral', while the target price is raised slightly from 60.6 to 60.8 euros.  The 1st half of the year showed a good operating performance in line with the excellent health of the market for the best Parisian offices, the core of SFL's portfolio. In fact, organic rental growth rose sharply by +10.1% against a backdrop of near-perfect occupancy rates (99.6%)", notes the analyst.Invest nevertheless points out that this performance was largely offset by the sharp rise in financial expenses (RNR/share, +1.8% to 1.16E). Over six months, NTA NAV is down -8.1%, due to a -4.1% drop in asset values, crystallizing a still too low yield of 3.4% (+35bp). As a result, further falls in asset values are highly likely (-16% by the end of 2024, according to Invest Securities estimates).  Nevertheless, its large pipeline of projects (900mE by 2026) and good debt profile should enable RNR to post a good medium-term growth profile (including +6.1% in 2023 and +10.6% in 2024)', stresses the broker. title: WDH/AKTIEN IM FOKUS :  Porsche and Volkswagen have run out of steam
full_text: (Repeat for technical reasons.)      FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - Following Porsche AG 's quarterly report, the three shares related to Volkswagen found themselves among the price losers in the Dax on Wednesday. The papers of Porsche AG, Porsche Holding and Volkswagen each lost almost two percent.      "Investors have priced a great deal of optimism into the valuation of companies in recent trading weeks," wrote Borsen expert Andreas Lipkow in a market commentary. This high expectation could now hardly be met. "Whether it's the quarterly figures from Porsche or LVMH, investors are showing rather disappointed faces everywhere," Lipkow said.      Operationally, Porsche AG was quite convincing, was the view of analysts on Wednesday. Philippe Houchois of Jefferies, for example, attested to the Stuttgart-based company's pleasingly high profitability in the second quarter. Jose Asumendi of JPMorgan pointed out that Porsche had increased its operating profit by almost eleven percent over the year despite higher costs./bek/zb

title: ESSILORLUXOTTICA :  UBS leaves its target unchanged
full_text: Following the announcement of its results, the analyst believes that sales were higher in Q2, thanks to Europe, but highlights the weakening of the US. Margins are in line with expectations, according to the analyst firm.UBS confirms its Neutral recommendation on the value and leaves its price target unchanged at 187 E.' Group Q2 sales of €6,699 million were 1% ahead of consensus and UBS forecasts, with Q2 growth of +8.0%. H1 2023 adjusted EBIT of 2,347 ME was +1% above consensus (in line with UBSe), with an EBIT margin of 18.3% (consensus 18.1%, UBSe 18%) ' says UBS.The Company has confirmed its annual sales growth target of around 5% between 2022 and 2026 at constant exchange rates (based on pro forma 2021 sales), and aims to achieve adjusted operating income of around 19-20% of sales by the end of this period.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: LVMH :  Oddo BHF raises its price target
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its 'outperform' rating on LVMH shares, with its target price raised from 875 to 907 euros, despite slightly lower EBIT forecasts for 2023-2025.Last night, the group published sales of 42,240 ME for the 1st half of the year, representing +17% organic growth (with Q2 at +17%, keeping pace with Q1), and EBIT of 11,574 ME, up 13%.7 Oddo BHF was expecting 42,339 ME and 11,732 ME respectively.The analyst also announces a slight reduction in EBIT forecasts (-1%), while EPS forecasts remain unchanged overall. Nevertheless, Oddo BHF believes that LVMH is in a position to maintain average annual EBIT growth of more than 10% over 2023-2025 'The absence of any major positive surprise on the topline and the slight squeeze on the group EBIT margin over the half-year due to the effect of marketing expenditure can be considered rather disappointing', says Oddo BHF. Nevertheless, 'beyond the China effect from one quarter to the next, the luxury goods sector as a whole is now beginning to normalize its growth rate, and it is logical that the potential for positive surprises should diminish in this context', acknowledges the analyst's office. title: DASSAULT SYSTÈMES :  Invest Securities does not return to buy
full_text: The analyst believes that the stock's decline (-5%) does not provide sufficient potential to return to buy. Invest Securities reiterates its Neutral opinion on the stock, with a target price of E40.' It's a pity, as we consider the stock market reaction to Medidata's temporary slowdown to be disproportionate, given that (i) growth in this business is set to return to >+10% from Q4 23, and (ii) management has a track record that argues in its favor, as evidenced by its talk of China in Q1 23, which has been verified in Q2 23' says the analyst firm.  Without the valuation criterion holding us back, we would be positive on the stock in view of (i) the exciting organic outlook for CT and MT and (ii) the additional M&A leverage enabled by the group's total deleveraging (acquisition capacity >5bnE)' adds Invest Securities.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: SFL :  Invest Securities raises its recommendation
full_text: Invest Securities has raised its recommendation on Foncière Lyonnaise (SFL) shares from 'sell' to 'neutral', following a drop in the share price, while the target price has been raised slightly, from 60.6 to 60.8 euros.  The 1st half of the year showed a good operating performance in line with the excellent health of the market for the best Parisian offices, the core of SFL's portfolio. In fact, organic rental growth rose sharply by +10.1% against a backdrop of near-perfect occupancy rates (99.6%)", notes the analyst.Invest nevertheless points out that this performance was largely offset by the sharp rise in financial expenses (RNR/share, +1.8% to 1.16E). Over six months, NTA NAV is down -8.1%, due to a -4.1% drop in asset values, crystallizing a still too low yield of 3.4% (+35bp). As a result, further falls in asset values are highly likely (-16% by the end of 2024, according to Invest Securities estimates).  Nevertheless, its large pipeline of projects (900mE by 2026) and good debt profile should enable RNR to post a good medium-term growth profile (including +6.1% in 2023 and +10.6% in 2024)', stresses the broker. title: ASSYSTEM :  Invest Securities remains Buy, adjusts its target
full_text: Invest Securities reaffirms its 'buy' opinion on Assystem, with an adjusted price target of €55 to €56, believing that 'more than ever, the stock remains a strong conviction to benefit from the nuclear revival'.'Quarter after quarter, achievements confirm that the acceleration in nuclear business growth will be faster than initially envisaged', judges the analyst, for whom second-quarter organic growth reflects this dynamic. Invest Securities also welcomes the slight increase in 2023 targets, as well as the positive message on recruitment and the decline in turnover. The only uncertainty lies in the timing of the disposal of our stakes in Expleo and Framatome," he adds.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com.
