title: EXANE BNP CHANGES SIDES :  Adidas now favorite, Inditex and Nike downgraded
full_text: PARIS (dpa-AFX) - A settlement between Europe's athletic footwear giant Adidas and fashion market leader Inditex has triggered a change of sides at French investment bank Exane BNP Paribas. In addition, the stock of Adidas competitor Nike was also downgraded.      After he had given clear preference to Zara parent Inditex twelve months ago, Adidas shares are now his favorite, analyst Warwick Okines wrote in a study available on Tuesday. Accordingly, he upgraded the stock of German sporting goods maker Adidas to "outperform" from "neutral" and raised his price target to 210 euros from 170 euros. At the same time, he lowered his investment rating for Inditex from "outperform" to "neutral" and maintained his price target of 36 euros.      The upside potential for Adidas would thus currently still be around 14 percent, after the share is currently up almost 6 percent following key figures, raised annual targets and the Exane study. For Inditex, the maintained price target would still mean an upside potential of just under 6 percent.      A year ago, he compared Adidas and Inditex, and the earnings performance of the two could not have been more different since then. While Adidas' profits were dwindling, Inditex had consistently beaten forecasts and increased profits. Now, however, the tide is turning, he wrote.      After re-evaluating social media data, app usage and internet searches, he concluded: The Adidas brand is picking up steam again. As the brand gains momentum, Okines believes the company can quickly recover profitability. "Gross margins should strengthen earnings power in the process," he expects. His earnings estimate for 2024, for example, is now about 30 percent higher than the average expectation in the market.      Looking at Inditex, which includes the brands Zara, Massimo Dutti and Bershka, Okines now sees little scope for increasing forecasts. Ebit margins are back at a ten-year high, he said, and the company's borse value is near record levels.      At Adidas competitor Nike, demand is cooling off, the Exane analyst also quotes his colleagues in the US. These downgraded the shares of the U.S. sporting goods manufacturer this Tuesday from "Neutral" to "Underweight" and cut the price target by 7 U.S. dollars to 92 dollars.      With an "outperform" rating, analysts at Exane BNP Paribas expect the stock to outperform the sector over the next twelve months. According to them, the share should develop in line with the sector with a rating of "Neutral", while "Underperform" means that the stock should develop worse than the sector. A period of twelve months always applies./ck/bek/jha/  Publication of the original studies: 07/25/2023

title: METZLER :  Conti can herald a turnaround at the end of the year - No 'Sell' anymore
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - Continental should herald a turnaround for the better in the fourth quarter, according to Bankhaus Metzler. Margins should then recover and more cash should be generated, analyst Pal Skirta wrote in a study presented on Monday. The latter would then also return to pre-crisis levels. The expert therefore upgraded the shares of the automotive supplier and tire manufacturer from "Sell" to "Hold" and raised the price target from 50.00 to 73.60 euros. The shares are currently trading at just over 74 euros.      The Capital Markets Day next winter could become a driving force for the share price, Skirta continued. This is because at this event the company will probably explain its strategy in more detail, on the one hand, and raise its medium-term targets, on the other. The medium-term future is likely to depend to a large extent on the extent to which the corporation is able to earn money with its research and development pipeline in the automotive division.      According to the analyst, Continental is at a crossroads, as its future market shares are threatened by the global upheavals in the automotive industry. This, he said, is forcing the corporation to innovate even in the long-established tire segment.      However, Skirta is cautious about 2023. The implementation of the rebuild is likely to weigh on the investment background for the time being. However, the expert does not expect a profit warning. Rather, he says, Continental is on track to meet its full-year forecasts. However, in view of the looming recession and the ongoing inflationary pressure, the chances of raising the forecast are likely to be slim.      Rated "Hold," Bankhaus Metzler expects the company's share price to remain largely stable over the next twelve months./la/ag/jha/      Analyzing institute Metzler Capital Markets. title: ICADE :  Oddo BHF reiterates its recommendation on the share
full_text: For Foncière Tertiaire (89% CF 2022), rental revenues came to 181 ME in H1 2023, representing pc growth of 2.2% yoy (vs. +2.8% in Q1 23 and -0.4% over 2022), says Oddo BHF in its analysis of the dayOn a like-for-like basis, revenues were down 2.1% yoy due to disposals in 2022 and H1 23.Leasing activity was brisk, with the signing of 46 leases covering some 100,000m² for a face rent of 27 ME and an average firm term of 6.4 years, the research firm points out.' On the balance sheet side, EPRA NTA NAV/share came to E79.3, down 11.8% on H1 23, mainly due to the pc decline in asset valuation of 6.7% in the Tertiary segment '. A new strategic plan is expected by early 2024. Oddo BHF confirms its Outperform rating, with a price target of E61.  We believe that Icade has the right fundamentals following the sale of Icade Santé to enter the new real estate cycle," adds the research firm.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Metzler Raises Continental AG to 'Hold' and Target to 73.60 Euros
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - Bankhaus Metzler upgraded Continental to "hold" from "sell" and raised its price target to 73.60 euros from 50.00 euros. The auto supplier and tire maker should reach a turning point in the fourth quarter, with margin recovery and rising cash generation, analyst Pal Skirta wrote in a research note Monday. The capital market day in winter could become a price driver./edh/mis  Publication of the original study: 24.07.2023 / 07:56 / CEST First disclosure of the original study: 24.07.2023 / 07:56 / CEST----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX Broker) - U.S. bank JPMorgan cut its price target for Sartorius to 405 euros from 415 euros, but kept its rating at "overweight." title: Eiffage: share price up, a broker's analysis
full_text: Eiffage gained just over 1% in Paris as APRR reported a 4.2% increase in traffic in Q2 2023, marking an acceleration on the +1.8% achieved in Q1 2023.Over the 1st half, traffic is up by 3%", points out Oddo BHF, which confirms its Outperform recommendation and its target of 124 euros for the share."Light vehicles are driving growth over the quarter, with an increase of +4.9% in Q2 (after 1.9% in Q1). On the other hand, growth is more timid in heavy goods vehicles, with an increase of just +0.5% after +1.5% in Q1 2023', says the research firm.Oddo BHF expects sales for the Eiffage Group to rise by 10% to 10,409 ME, with EBIT up 10% to 1,050 ME and net income up 15% in H1 2023 compared with H1 2022.'We have marginally adjusted our 2023 estimates to incorporate a good H1/Q2. Our Operating Profit stands at 2,372 ME, in line with the consensus of 2,356 ME' adds Oddo BHF.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. All rights reserved.

title: UBISOFT :  Deutsche Bank raises its price target
full_text: On Friday, Deutsche Bank raised its price target for Ubisoft from 35 to 40 euros, while maintaining its buy recommendation on the stock.In a research note, the analyst points out that last night, the video game group reported net sales excluding certain deferred income ('net bookings') of 268 million for the first quarter of its offbeat fiscal year.This figure, he points out, is 12% higher than the target set by the group (240 million euros) and 4% higher than the average consensus estimate.It shows a decline of 8% at constant exchange rates, and represents one of the worst quarters in the Group's history", he points out."That said, this item was widely expected due to the absence of high-profile title launches during the quarter", recalls the professional.According to DB, the most important thing is that Ubisoft has confirmed its financial targets for fiscal 2023/2024, starting with "strong growth" in sales: where the consensus forecasts 23%, the analyst predicts an increase of 26%.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: VIVENDI :  Oddo BHF confirms its recommendation on the share
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its "outperform" rating on Vivendi shares, with an unchanged target price of 13 euros. Yesterday, Canal+ announced the acquisition of a 12% stake in Viaplay, a pay-TV specialist operating mainly in Sweden, Norway, Denmark and Finland. Viaplay is also expanding internationally via its OTT offering (11 markets in total and ~2.6 M subscribers).Even if it is only a very small stake for the moment, this acquisition is in line with Canal+'s strategy of strengthening its pay-TV activities in Europe, analyzes Oddo BHF.'Vivendi's pay-TV strategy is therefore aimed at achieving complete continental coverage. Viaplay would add a Nordic dimension to Vivendi's strategy", concludes the analyst.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX) - U.S. bank JPMorgan cut its price target for SAP to 138 euros from 140 euros after quarterly results, but left its rating at "overweight." title: EIFFAGE :  Oddo BHF remains Buy after APRR figures
full_text: APRR has reported a 4.2% increase in traffic in Q2 2023, marking an acceleration on the +1.8% achieved in Q1 2023.  Over the 1st half, traffic was up by 3.0%, below the performance observed at Sanef (+3.8% in H1, including +3.4% in Q1)' stresses Oddo BHF.Following the announcement of these figures, Oddo BHF confirms its Outperform recommendation and its target of 124 E.' Growth in the quarter was driven by light vehicles, with an increase of +4.9% in Q2 (after 1.9% in Q1). On the other hand, growth is more timid in heavy goods vehicles, with an increase of just +0.5% after +1.5% in Q1 2023' says the research firm.Oddo BHF expects sales for the Eiffage Group to rise by 10% to 10,409 ME, with EBIT up 10% to 1,050 ME and net income up 15% in H1 2023 compared with H1 2022. ' The Group should confirm its annual guidance of ' a further increase in its operating income in Works and Concessions ' and an increase in net income, thanks in particular to the integration of Getlink by the equity method from Q2 2023. We have marginally adjusted our 2023 estimates to take into account a good H1/Q2. Our Operating Profit stands at 2,372 ME, in line with the consensus of 2,356 ME' adds Oddo BHF.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: DASSAULT AVIATION :  Stifel confirms its recommendation on the stock
full_text: Stifel maintains its Buy rating on Dassault Aviation shares, with an unchanged target price of 240 euros. Following last night's results, the analyst believes that 'the French aircraft manufacturer's results for the first half of 2023 may appear disappointing'. He points out that the company took few orders, delivered very few aircraft, recorded a 26% drop in sales and consumed almost €2 billion in cash."In reality, these figures reflect the ramp-up in production and are, in our view, the prelude to sales taking off. Order intake should rebound strongly in the second half of the year, taking the order backlog to 8 years' sales", says Stifel.Against this backdrop, the broker expects EPS to rise. We estimate that by the end of the year, the order book should total more than 230 Rafales and almost 90 Falcon jets", concludes the research firm.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: DASSAULT AVIATION :  Oddo BHF raises its target price
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its Outperform rating on Dassault Aviation shares, with a price target raised from 205 to 214 euros.  Last night, Dassault Aviation published half-year earnings 9% below Oddo BHF's expectations in terms of operating income, and 2% below the VA consensus, mainly due to a shift in deliveries to the 2nd half of 2023.  This slight disappointment on H1 2023 EBIT is largely offset by the confirmation of the guidance of 35 Falcon and 15 Rafale deliveries over 2023 as a whole, with a strong concentration on H2, as well as by financial income well above our expectations", adds the analyst. title: NEXANS :  BofA renews buy recommendation after EuroAsia contract win
full_text: Bank of America on Thursday renewed its Buy recommendation and 100 euro price target on Nexans, deeming the 'record' EuroAsia Interconnector contract win an important step in the stock's recovery.From the analyst's point of view, this order estimated at over 1.4 billion euros represents a 'key moment' for the cable manufacturer, confirming its ambitious targets in high-voltage networks by 2024.For the intermediary, this agreement also shows that Nexans remains the best possible choice for investors wishing to play the energy transition theme within the cable sector.Finally, BofA refers to an "attractive" valuation, with the stock currently trading at a discount of around 35% to the sector and underperforming the STOXX Europe 600 sector index by 18% since the beginning of the year.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - DZ Bank downgraded Hellofresh from "hold" to "sell" and lowered the fair value from 23 to 20 euros. title: EDENRED :  Deutsche Bank raises its target price
full_text: Deutsche Bank raised its target price for Edenred on Thursday from €67 to €68, seeing continued upside potential in the stock despite the French group's slowing growth.The German bank, which is maintaining its buy recommendation on the stock, says it expects the prepaid services specialist to report half-year sales up 23.7% to €1.14 billion on July 25.With regard to Ebitda, DB expects first-half earnings of €470 million, above the consensus target of €464 million.In terms of debt, Edenred should see its debt rise to 1.2 billion euros at the end of June, compared with 307 million euros at the end of 2022, due to the acquisition of Reward Gateway, adds the German establishment.In terms of outlook, while Edenred has set itself the target of increasing its like-for-like Ebitda by more than 12% over the medium term, the consensus is for growth this year of between 17.5% and 25.5%, emphasizes Deutsche Bank.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: ARGAN :  Oddo BHF reduces its target price
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its 'outperform' rating on Argan shares, with a downward revision of its target price from 93 to 84 euros, due in particular to a faster-than-expected decline in asset values. Yesterday evening, Argan published quarterly results in line with its growth trajectory, with CEO recurring net income of E62.8 bn and continuation EPRA Net Asset Value (NTA) down -16% over 6 months to E78.1 (vs. NDV NAV of E85.3) following the revaluation of assets to E3.64 bn vs. E3.94 bn at end 2022.Finally, Argan confirms its guidance with an expected RNR 2023 of 124 ME and raises its 2023 dividend target to 3.15 E vs. at least 3.00 E previously', says Oddo BHF. title: Wacker Chemie investors also put profit warning well away
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - The next piece of bad news from the chemical industry was again absorbed quite well by investors on Wednesday. With Wacker Chemie, another group had to trim its targets for the full year, which pushed the shares four percent into the red at the start of trading on the stock exchange on Wednesday. However, the share price managed to turn around at the 200-day line and at times even edged upwards. Most recently, they were again moderately in the red with 0.3 percent.      Recently, other sector stocks had also hardly reacted after bad news. Profit warnings from chemical companies have recently become the rule because of sour demand, which is associated with the reduction of inventories. Borsianer therefore already wondered in the morning whether the news from Wacker will again sustainably weigh. Sebastian Satz of Barclays Bank expressed his suspicion, in view of the early price losses, that there had certainly been hope in the market that Wacker would avoid a warning.      Many analysts stressed that the extent of the target reduction was a negative surprise compared to consensus. Markus Mayer of Baader Bank, however, qualified the significance of this somewhat. He had recently held many discussions with investors - with the conclusion that expectations for Ebitda this year had already been lowered below the one billion euro mark. The "shadow consensus" had thus probably been below that of analysts and this should contain the share price reaction as observed on Wednesday.      "Since we assume that the profit trend will bottom out in 2023 and that Wacker will also benefit from solar claims and subsidized electricity prices, we recommend investors to take advantage of a perhaps significant price weakness to buy," the Baader expert had recommended before the stock market launch.      Mayer and his JPMorgan colleague Chetan Udeshi calculated that the mean value of the new target range, which has now been put at 0.8 and 1.0 billion euros, is 19 percent below consensus estimates. The previously advised range had been up to 1.4 billion euros. Udeshi expects the consensus to fall by 15 percent. Cuts are also likely again in 2024, he said.      Barclays expert Satz called it a "significant target reduction," driven primarily by weak demand for silicone products. "The company benefited from extreme tightness and strong demand in early 2022 and now faces the opposite," the expert argued. Meanwhile, the polysilicon business, which is important for the semiconductor and solar industries, is doing better than feared, he said.      The fact that Wacker Chemie fared better than the sector was recently already priced into the share price: The shares have already gained more than a fifth since the June low, which is significantly more than the pan-European index for the chemical industry, which has gained a maximum of five percent in a similar period. However, the sector index remained on its stabilization course on Wednesday, moving 0.4 percent higher and again attempting to jump above its 100-day average.BASF, for example, gained a good one percent on Wednesday to a high for more than a month. Evonik, however, saw a one percent drop after its shares were downgraded to "underweight" by Morgan Stanley. Compared with the sector, they had also recovered more than average by up to 13 percent since the low in mid-June.Covestro also showed weakness with a discount of 1.8 percent. However, takeover fantasies have been playing a bigger role here recently: according to circles, the oil group Abu Dhabi National Oil (Adnoc) wants to increase its bid for the Dax group from the previously rumored 55 to 57 euros per share. The share price came back on Wednesday after briefly jumping the previous evening. The current price below 50 euros suggests that investors are skeptical about the speculation./tih/ag/stk

title: Kering: share price rises sharply, SG upgrades to buy
full_text: Kering recorded the biggest rise in the CAC 40 index on the Paris Bourse on Wednesday, after Société Générale upgraded its recommendation on the stock to 'buy'.Shortly before 2:00 pm, the French luxury goods group's shares gained 5.4%, while the leading index rose by just 0.3%.SG has raised its recommendation to 'buy' from 'hold', with a price target raised from 460 to 650 euros, reflecting a potential upside of almost 32% compared with Tuesday's closing price.In their note, analysts point out that the stock was trading yesterday evening at a P/E discount of around 45% compared with the rest of the stocks they follow.The research firm also points to an "unprecedented" discount to the MSCI sector index, which it attributes to market concerns over the Gucci brand's turnaround and the evolution of the management team.On the latter point, the appointments of Francesca Bellettini, CEO of Yves Saint Laurent, as Deputy CEO of Kering in charge of the development of the houses, and of CFO Jean-Marc Duplaix as Deputy CEO in charge of operations and finance, should reassure investors, SG believes.On the stock market, Kering shares are up 9% since the start of the year, compared with a 13.5% gain for the CAC.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. full_text: HAMBURG (dpa-AFX Broker) - Private bank Berenberg has left Stratec on "Hold" with a price target of 62 euros after figures and lowered forecasts. The diagnostics specialist reported a weak first half and revised its full-year targets significantly downward, analyst Odysseas Manesiotis wrote in a research note published on Wednesday. Earnings per share expectations for 2023 are now expected to fall by around 20 percent. According to Manesiotis, the news from Stratec suggests negative conclusions for Biomerieux in particular, and to a lesser extent for Qiagen, Diasorin and Tecan. Stratec is known for comparatively optimistic targets, he said. title: PUBLICIS :  Oddo BHF adjusts its target price
full_text: While reiterating its 'neutral' opinion, Oddo BHF has adjusted its target price for Publicis from €73 to €72, the day after the publication of its American peer Omnicom's quarterly results, marked by organic growth slightly below expectations.While Publicis is expected to generate 61% of its sales in North America, it should be negatively impacted by the euro's very recent rise against the US currency", believes the analyst, who is updating his annual estimates accordingly.For 2023, based on the spot rate, Oddo BHF is therefore revising its 2023/24 EBITA guidance downwards by 3%. title: KERING :  Oddo BHF remains neutral ahead of half-year results
full_text: Last night, the Group announced two major management changes. Following this announcement, Oddo BHF confirms its neutral recommendation on the stock, with a target price of E498.The group's central management will be strengthened with the promotion to deputy CEO of Jean Marc Duplaix (current CFO), who will be in charge of finance and operations, and Francesca Belletini (CEO Saint Laurent), who will be in charge of brand development, says Oddo BHF.' The management of the Gucci Group's main brand (which alone accounts for almost 70% of its EBIT) is set to change with the departure of Marco Bizzarri, effective September 23. He will be replaced, for a transitional period, by Jean François Palus', stresses the analyst firm. The analyst believes that the change at the head of Gucci seems to suggest that, since the conviction has recently been acquired that Gucci could not recover as desired in its current structure, Jean François Palus will be expected to improve the brand's operations and prepare for the future. ' We may have to wait for a new appointment to see just how much things will change,' reckons Oddo BHF.  The stock is highly discounted, but Gucci's financial trajectory remains particularly uncertain at this stage: we are not convinced that the current efforts undertaken are sufficient to ensure a recovery, but the amplitude and nature of the changes to come remain difficult to anticipate at this stage.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: CASINO :  Oddo BHF maintains 'underperform' rating
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its underperform rating on Casino shares, with an unchanged target price of 0.05 euros. The research firm reports that, following the withdrawal of the 3F group, only the Kretinsky/Fimalac/Attestor bid has been submitted.  Attestor, which was initially allied with 3F, has now joined forces with Kretinsky/Fimalac (and may be sued at a later date)', adds the analyst. Oddo BHF believes that the offer is slightly more favorable to existing shareholders, who are diluted to 0.3% of the capital compared with 0.2% in the previous offer.In addition, the debt reduction is lower, at E4.7 bn compared with E5.0 bn in the first offer, so that the company will be c. 300 ME more leveraged.While the new offer is slightly more attractive for shareholders than the first, the dilution will be massive, and the 108 million current shares will be replaced by several tens of billions of new shares after debt restructuring", concludes the analyst. title: JPMorgan leaves Hugo Boss at 'Neutral' - Target 80 euros
full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX Broker) - U.S. bank JPMorgan left Hugo Boss at "Neutral" with a price target of 80 euros. The latest quarterly reports from European luxury goods groups Swatch, Burberry and Richemont brought few surprises in terms of sales and rather disappointed the already high expectations, analyst Chiara Battistini wrote in an industry report available on Tuesday. Hugo Boss, meanwhile, is in the early stages of a sales turnaround under a new boss, she added. She appreciated the new strategic focus on growth and market share gains. However, it said the fashion group is very dependent on the European consumer, who is struggling with a more difficult environment and high cost of living, which is not making it any easier for Boss./gl/la      Publication of the original study: 17.07.2023 / 19:44 / BST First disclosure of the original study: 18.07.2023 / 00:15 / BST----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: SES-IMAGOTAG :  Berenberg reiterates its buy recommendation
full_text: Berenberg - which had briefly placed its recommendation on SES-imagotag 'under review' - this morning reiterated its 'buy' recommendation on the stock, with a new target price of €215, up from the previous €175.In its research note, the German bank believes that investors should be prepared for a resurgence of buying interest in the stock following the recent accusations made by the US Gotham fund.In our view, the consensus does not fully reflect the margin-increasing nature of its penetration rate in a high-value-added segment, nor its growing market adoption, particularly in the US", explains the financial institution.Its new price target shows a potential upside of around 73% compared with Monday evening's closing price.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: CBO TERRITORIA :  Invest Securities lowers its target
full_text: Invest Securities maintains its buy recommendation on CBO Territoria shares, with a slightly reduced target price, from 4.1 to 3.9 euros, due to more conservative forecasts. The 2022 financial year had proved exceptional, with a very sharp rise in restated RNR 2022 (+23.7%, 0.55E/share), recalls the analyst.In addition, the hoarding of earnings had enabled NAV to rise by +5.5% (6.63E/share).  CBo's "fonciarisation" is proceeding without major risks, but we do note a greater degree of caution (in the development business and in terms of the impact of rising interest rates in particular)", says the analyst.  Despite the somewhat costly new ORNANE issue (15ME, 7% coupon), which has the merit of maintaining a diversification of financing sources, the company's distribution capacity (0.24E in 2022) does not seem to us to be under threat', adds Invest.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: FORVIA  :  Berenberg raises its target price
full_text: Berenberg - which has a buy recommendation on Forvia - on Monday raised its target price for the stock from €25 to €28, for which analysts still see upside potential.In a research note published this morning, the broker anticipates positive surprises when the group publishes its first-half results, scheduled for July 27.The broker anticipates a possible upward revision of sales and cash flow targets for 2023, thanks in particular to good pricing and better-than-expected business volumes in China.Despite the stock's solid performance since the start of the year, we continue to believe that there is still upside potential due to the combination of attractive long-term fundamentals and a relatively defensive margin and cash flow profile in the shorter term", summarizes Berenberg.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: ORPEA  :  AlphaValue reduces its target further
full_text: AlphaValue announced on Monday that it had reduced its target price for Orpea shares from 0.19 to 0.18 euros, following the downward revision of the group's targets announced last week.In a research note, the research firm fears a "complicated" turnaround following the resounding scandal surrounding the methods used by the specialist in accommodation for the dependent elderly.Last week, the group announced that it had lowered its operating performance targets for 2023, citing insufficient occupancy rates in a "still difficult" reputational context, as well as higher staff costs, a factor it explained as part of its drive to improve support and care for its residents.In view of this gloomy outlook, AlphaValue is maintaining its negative opinion on the stock, i.e. a sell recommendation, saying that it anticipates efforts to be much more intense than initially expected.The only small reason for relief according to the research cabiner is that operating performance could be slightly bolstered by positive non-recurring tax items, as well as by a reduction in capital expenditure.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. full_text: On Monday, Stifel raised its price target on Dassault Aviation shares, which it still considers 'undervalued' despite its recent stock market outperformance.In a research note, the financial intermediary points out that the aircraft manufacturer's shares have 'clearly outperformed' mid-cap stocks over the past nine months, gaining over 20%.The analyst attributes this feat to the aerospace group's solid results and fundamentals, but above all to the Rafale's "exceptional" development prospects, against a backdrop of tensions in Ukraine and Taiwan.The order book could approach a level representing eight years of activity by the end of the year, a factor which has not yet been taken into account in the share price", he points out.According to Stifel, the market has also failed to take into account the company's 25% stake in Thales, estimated at some 7.1 billion euros, and a net cash position that should reach 12.4 billion euros by the end of 2023.The professional, who maintains his buy recommendation on the share, consequently raises his target price on the stock from 185 to 240 euros.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Forvia: share price advances, analyst sees potential
full_text: Forvia escaped the downward trend on the Paris Bourse on Monday morning, following encouraging comments from Berenberg analysts, who said they still saw potential in the stock.At around 9:50 a.m., the automotive equipment supplier's shares were up by more than 0.2%, while the SBF 120 index was losing nearly 0.3% at the same time.In a research note published in the morning, Berenberg said it expects positive surprises when the group publishes its first-half results, scheduled for July 27.The German bank anticipates a possible upward revision of sales and cash flow targets for 2023, thanks in particular to good pricing and better-than-expected business volumes in China.Despite the stock's solid performance since the start of the year, we continue to believe that there is still upside potential, given the combination of attractive long-term fundamentals and a relatively defensive margin and cash flow profile in the shorter term", summarizes Berenberg.The firm - which has a Buy recommendation on the stock - is therefore raising its target price from €25 to €28.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. All rights reserved.

full_text: Oddo BHF remains 'underperform' on Rémy Cointreau, with its price target lowered from 135 to 131 euros, pointing to a BNIC report which states that 'a return to growth in the cognac market is only expected in early 2024 and under certain conditions'.The analyst warns: "The adjustment of the consensus on the topline could continue after the publication of sales for the first quarter of 2023/24 (07/25/2023), and open the debate on the guidance of a stable operating margin on a like-for-like basis".In the longer term, the Group could lose all its advance on the 2030 strategic plan, which is reflected in our sales estimate, which we have lowered to -4% on a like-for-like basis over 2023/24, compared with a consensus of -0.7%", he continues.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: JPMorgan downgrades Brenntag due to particularly high earnings risks
full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX) - According to U.S. bank JPMorgan, Brenntag has been hit particularly hard by the gloomy business outlook in the chemicals industry. Therefore, analyst Chetan Udeshi downgraded the chemicals trader's stock from "Neutral" to "Underweight" and lowered the price target from 83 to 66 euros in an industry report available on Friday. This is almost five percent below the current level.      The continuing weakness in demand in the chemical sector, reflected in numerous profit warnings, together with the increasingly weaker price trends, raises the risk of an unexpectedly massive earnings normalization, also among distributors, the expert fears. He says his estimates for adjusted operating earnings (Ebitda) for Brenntag and rivals IMCD and Azelis in 2023 and 2024 are below consensus forecasts.      At Brenntag, Udeshi sees particularly high earnings risks due to its strong exposure to the basic chemicals market, where pricing pressure is stronger. He also complained the company is not seeing volume growth compared to 2019. The earnings performance in recent quarters also indicates that the quality of Brenntag's specialty chemicals business is significantly lower than that of IMCD and Azelis, the expert added. This reduces the potential for a spin-off of this business in the near future, he added.      Among the other two sector stocks, the expert prefers Azelis to IMCD due to its cheaper valuation. He therefore rates the two stocks as "Overweight" and "Neutral", respectively. The medium- to long-term growth prospects in the sector remain attractive and offer considerable scope for value-enhancing acquisitions.      According to the "Underweight" rating, JPMorgan expects the stock to underperform the respective sector in the coming six to twelve months. "Overweight," on the other hand, means the stock should outperform during that time. "Neutral," in the bank's view, suggests a trend in line with the respective sector./gl/tih/jha/      Analyzing institute JPMorgan. title: AIRBUS :  Oddo BHF confirms its Buy recommendation
full_text: Oddo BHF expects a solid 2nd quarter 2023 (publication on July 26), with Adjusted EBIT up 28% on the 2nd quarter 2022, mainly driven by Airbus Commercial.  In this segment, we expect Adjusted EBIT of 1,569 ME (+29.6%) on sales of 12.4 MdE, representing a margin of 12.7% (-80 bp or -72 bp excluding R&D and provision reversals), driven by i/ a strong volume effect, with the delivery of 34 additional aircraft compared with Q2 2022, including 29 A320s; ii/ a 5-cent improvement in the USD hedge; iii/ improved profitability of the A350 program, thanks to the delivery of 3 additional aircraft; and iv/ better amortization of fixed costs', says Oddo BHF.The analyst expects Adjusted FCF of 1,815 ME, higher than in Q2 2022, after consumption of 889 ME in Q1.  We are incrementally more confident about our estimate of 735 deliveries in 2023 (perhaps with the exception of the A220) and our forecast of 840 in 2024," adds the analyst.Oddo BHF confirms its Outperform recommendation on the share and its price target of 145 ECopyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: KAUFMAN & BROAD :  Oddo BHF reduces its target price
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its 'neutral' rating on Kaufman & Broad shares, with a price target reduced from 28 to 24.5 euros. Last night, Kaufman & Broad reported sales of €848.8 million for the first half, up 47.8% from €574.5 million a year earlier. This increase is in line with analysts' expectations (Oddo BHF was forecasting sales of ME 846), and can be explained by a stronger contribution from the Commercial division, with sales of ME 380.9 (ME 87.3 in H1 2022) due to the impact of the Austerlitz project, says Oddo BHF. On the other hand, the analyst points out that MOP came in slightly below expectations, at 8% versus 8.2% expected. Furthermore, Kaufman & Broad's management has adjusted its targets downwards, expecting sales to increase by 6% to 10% (i.e. around -5% compared with the previous estimate). Return on sales should remain unchanged at around 8%.Oddo BHF is therefore lowering its 2023 sales and ROE estimates by around -5%.'All in all, following this publication, our 2023e EPS have been lowered by 11%', says the broker, who nevertheless points out that 'the Austerlitz project is a major support factor. title: KALRAY :  Oddo BHF remains positive after a business update
full_text: Oddo BHF has reiterated its 'outperform' opinion and its price target of 38 euros on Kalray, following a publication in line with its expectations, which testifies to an initial acceleration in the commercial phase and reinforces its forecasts for 2023."The major new contracts signed in the first half and the ramp-up of the Dell partnership tend to lend further credibility to the company's objectives for the current financial year", believes the analyst in charge of the dossier. title: ATOS :  Oddo BHF raises its target price
full_text: Oddo BHF confirms its 'underperform' rating on Atos, but raises its price target from 12.7 to 13.1 euros, ahead of the IT services group's second-quarter publication, scheduled for July 28.The research firm slightly raises its organic growth forecast to +2% for the current quarter and +1.1% for the full year, but lowers its 2023 FCF forecast to -466 million euros (from -379 million).  Despite this resilience of the topline, the valuation seems to us to be too demanding, particularly in view of the Group's FCF generation", says the analyst, who also points to a fair value for Eviden alone, which he evaluates at just 13.4 euros per share.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Jefferies raises Infineon to 'Hold' and target to 40 euros
full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX Broker) - Analysts Jefferies upgraded Infineon from "underperform" to "hold" and raised its price target to 40 euros from 28 euros. title: MICHELIN :  recommendation downgraded by Jefferies
full_text: Jefferies downgrades its recommendation on Michelin from 'buy' to 'hold', with a price target lowered from 34 to 28 euros, representing a potential upside of 6% for the tiremaker's stock."We believe that Michelin's target market will continue to underperform, which could lead to an under-absorption of fixed costs", explains the broker, who reduces his 2023-25 estimates from 3% to 6% and stands 2 to 5% below consensus.Add to this management's inflated ambitions for external growth, and we find it hard to see the stock outperforming in the short term', adds Jefferies, which therefore prefers automotive suppliers Forvia and Valeo to Michelin.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: VINCI :  Oddo BHF confirms its recommendation on the stock
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its 'outperform' rating on Vinci shares, with an unchanged target price of 138 euros. While Vinci will publish its half-year results on July 28, the research firm anticipates 'a solid performance in Q2'.  Motorway concessions should confirm their good momentum, with sales up 4.5% in Q2 and H1. VINCI Airports will continue to improve, with sales up 60% in Q2 (+70% in H1)", says Oddo BHF. Specifically, the analyst expects half-year sales of E32.5 bn, operating income of E3.5 bn and net income of E2.2 bn.'The Group should maintain its annual guidance of a more modest increase in sales and operating income than in 2022', concludes Oddo BHF. title: Bernstein leaves Bayer at 'Outperform' - Target 89 euros
full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX Broker) - U.S. analyst firm Bernstein Research left its rating on Bayer at "Outperform" with a price target of 89 euros. The phrase "This time it's different" could actually apply under new Group CEO Bill Anderson, analyst Gunther Zechmann wrote in a research note presented on Monday. Activist shareholders were putting pressure, recent results had disappointed, so Anderson could well be thinking seriously about firing the "Consumer Health silver bullet," Zechmann said. He sees some strategic options for the consumer health business. The optimal case, he said, is a merger with competitor Haleon. title: UBS EXPERT :  Difficult German housing market slows down Scout24
full_text: ZURICH (dpa-AFX) - For the major Swiss bank UBS, the housing market in Germany remains a problem child. This remains under pressure in the coming year, warned UBS analyst Adam Berlin in a study presented on Monday. The real estate platform Scout 24 he predicts in it also because of increasing competition a weaker growth. The expert therefore issued a sell recommendation and downgraded the shares from "Neutral" to "Sell".      After the price increase this year by a fifth, the papers of the sales platform are more expensive than those of the competition - despite lower growth, the industry expert also criticized. He lowered the price target from 59 to 51.40 euros (currently: 53.56).      The German housing market is suffering from rising interest rates. Many people can no longer afford the high prices for property purchases or rents. UBS expert Berlin estimates that despite the difficult environment, many brokers will not react quickly enough and call lower prices to boost their business. The tense situation could also lead to a number of insolvencies among real estate agencies, Berlin fears.      Already in the second quarter, this development is likely to have an impact on Scout24 : The expert expects a smaller increase in revenues compared to the start of the year, partly because growth from business with brokers declined.      For the full year, Berlin expects growth of only ten percent compared to the Group's forecast of 12 percent, if the acquisition of real estate data provider Sprengnetter is excluded. The pace is also expected to slow further in 2024. Looking ahead to the coming year, Berlin also considers it less likely that Scout24 will again be able to push through price increases of ten percent as in previous years.      The expert therefore lowered his expectations for earnings per share in the coming year, which is five percent below current market forecasts. However, Berlin is certain that these should also fall significantly.      Meanwhile, he also sees serious competition in the classifieds portal of the Norwegian operator Adevinta, which recently also took over the corresponding business from Ebay. In the meantime, the portal is on a par with Scout24 in terms of rentals and comes second in terms of sales, Berlin noted.      With its "Sell" rating, UBS assumes that the total return of the share (price gain plus dividend) over a period of twelve months is at least six percent below the market return expected by UBS./tav/tih/jha/      Publication of the original study: 07.07.2023 / 19:07 / GMT First circulation of the original study: 07.07.2023 / 19:07 / GMT

title: VERALLIA :  Oddo BHF reduces its target on the stock
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its Outperform rating on Verallia shares, with a price target reduced from €50 to €47, 'on the basis of comparables and a DCF', explains the broker.According to the analyst, the 1st quarter will remain exceptional, with a mix/price effect of 40%, a dynamic that should continue in the 2nd quarter 'but to a lesser extent'.For the 2nd quarter, the broker anticipates sales of 1094.6 ME (+23.1%, of which +18% organic), or half-year sales of 2146.2 ME (+31%, +26.4% organic, mainly driven by the mix/price effect).  We are expecting Q2 EBITDA of 273 ME (+12.5% YoY), with a neutral spread that could be conservative. For the half-year as a whole, we therefore target EBITDA of 580.6 ME (+36.4% YoY), i.e. an EBITDA margin of 27.1% (vs 26% YoY, +110bp)', continues the analyst. Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: HERMÈS :  Oddo BHF confirms its outperform rating on the stock
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its Outperform rating on Hermès shares, with an unchanged target price of 2028 euros. The analyst believes that growth in Q2 will remain "very strong". The description of major trends by geographic region suggests fairly homogeneous growth in Q2, and overall in line with Q1, when it came out at +23% year-on-year at constant exchange rates. Oddo BHF reports that the Group is cautious for the future, but that its positioning is a guarantee of relative security. Against this backdrop, the broker is raising its annual EBIT estimates by 1% and EPS by 2%, while remaining relatively conservative on margins. According to Oddo BHF, the stock's resilient profile should be 'a clear advantage at a time when growth in the sector is set to slow'. Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Saint-Gobain: share price advances, analyst's favorite stock
full_text: On Friday, Saint-Gobain was one of the biggest risers on the Paris Bourse's CAC 40 index, after analysts at Stifel upgraded the stock to their favorite sector stock.At 12:30 pm, shares in the French building materials giant were up 1.4%, while the CAC was up just 0.5%.Stifel this morning upgraded its recommendation on the share to "buy", with a target price raised to 68 euros from 52 euros, representing a potential upside of almost 30% compared with Thursday's closing price.In a study, the analyst says he expects the European construction sector to return to its pre-2008 financial crisis valuation levels within one to three years, thanks to government support for decarbonization and energy renovation projects.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: HSBC sees less upside potential for United Internet
full_text: LONDON (dpa-AFX) - The British investment bank HSBC currently considers an above-average development of United Internet to be unlikely. Therefore, analyst Adam Fox-Rumley downgraded the papers of the telecom group from "Buy" to "Hold". He also reduced his free cash flow and earnings (Ebitda) forecasts for the years 2023 to 2025 and cut his price target from EUR 25 to EUR 15 (current price: EUR 12.50).      The share price drivers expected for the first half of the year, such as a recovery in Ionos shares or 1&1's 5G capital markets day, have so far failed to materialize, Fox-Rumley wrote in a report available Friday. While he still sees some value in the company, he believes the road to realizing this upside potential is rocky.      The expert explained that United Internet's revaluation now depends on the market's view of its subsidiary 1&1. The mobile provider's management currently seems confident that everything is going according to plan with the 5G network rollout. In contrast, the market still seems to be in a skeptical "show-me" mode, with the real test of the rollout pace coming in the fourth quarter and early 2024.      HSBC always rates such stocks as "hold" with a price target up to 5 percent above or below the current price./edh/tih/men     Analyzing institute HSBC.  Publication of the original study: 07/06/2023 / 17:34 / GMT First disclosure of the original study: 07.07.2023 / 02:17 / GMT

title: THALES :  Oddo BHF confirms its recommendation on the stock
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its neutral rating on Thales shares, with an unchanged target price of 137 euros. With Thales due to publish its Q1 results on July 21, Oddo BHF expects organic sales growth of 6.5% to ME 8633 (of which 9.2% in Q1 and 4.3% in Q2). The broker believes that profitability should be preserved, and models EBIT at 989 ME, i.e. a margin of 11.5% (+66 bp). For its part, Thales anticipates organic sales growth of between 4% and 7% and an EBIT margin of between 11.5% and 11.8%.'All in all, we think Thales may just tighten its targets for fiscal 2023 towards the top end of existing ranges', concludes Oddo BHF. title: HERMÈS :  Oddo BHF reiterates its recommendation ahead of the 2nd quarter
full_text: The analyst believes that 2nd-quarter growth will remain very strong. The Group is cautious for the future, but its positioning is a guarantee of relative security.  There will be no slowdown in the United States where, after Q1 at +19%, we can expect Q2 growth to remain well above 10%, and both Europe (Q1 at c.+24%) and Japan (Q1 +26%) should, in our opinion, continue to grow above +20% in Q2', says Oddo BHF.' In the Asia-Pacific region, the acceleration in growth in Q2 compared with Q1 (+22.5%) due to China is likely to be slightly less marked than for the rest of the sector, as Hermès held up much better than its peers in China in Q2 last year (with a strong acceleration in June)' adds the research house.The absence of any noticeable slowdown in Europe/Japan/Americas has led the analyst to raise its Q2 growth forecast (y/y cc) from 19.3% to 23.8% (the most recent Visible Alpha consensus is c.+23%, says Oddo BHF).  We remain relatively cautious on H2 growth (Q3 forecast raised from +7.7% to 9.1%, but still showing a noticeable slowdown, Q4 forecast virtually unchanged at +12.1%), hence an increase in our annual growth assumption from +15.2% to +16.6%. For 2024, Oddo BHF is still forecasting growth of around +12%, reflecting a price premium over the rest of the sector that the analyst evaluates at c. +300 bp. Oddo confirms its Outperform recommendation on the stock, with a target price of E2028.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Baader Bank leaves Thyssenkrupp at 'Buy' - Target 16 euros
full_text: MUNICH (dpa-AFX Broker) - Baader Bank has left Thyssenkrupp at "Buy" with a price target of 16 euros on the occasion of the initial public offering (IPO) of Nucera. The now upcoming IPO of the hydrogen subsidiary is positive for the industrial group, as it reduces the complexity of the company's structure and puts a price tag on an important growth business, analyst Christian Obst wrote in a research note presented Friday. In addition, the move should make Nucera more attractive to potential new customers and employees. The expert believes Nucera can be valued at up to 3.5 billion euros within 12 to 18 months. At today's price, the market capitalization is around 2.5 billion euros./gl/tih      Publication of the original study: 07.07.2023 / 07:24 / CEST First disclosure of the original study: Date not stated in study / Time not stated in study / Time zone not stated in study----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: EURONEXT :  Deutsche Bank downgrades its recommendation to 'hold
full_text: Deutsche Bank announced on Thursday that it had downgraded its recommendation on Euronext from "buy" to "hold", with a price target lowered from 103 to 69 euros due to the lack of catalysts around the stock.In a note sent to its clients, the financial intermediary acknowledges that the stock exchange operator has done a "good job" over the past ten years in developing and diversifying its activities.Nevertheless, it points out that the cash equity markets and related businesses (clearing and settlement) continue to represent a major part of the Group's business, with the associated volatility in terms of results.In view of the current sluggish market environment, DB is forecasting a further quarter of negative growth in the second quarter of 2023, in terms of both revenues and earnings.In view of this unfavorable dynamic, the analyst prefers to downgrade his recommendation on the stock, despite a valuation deemed "cheap" compared to its peers, with a PER of 11.5x by 2024.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: LISI :  Oddo BHF raises its target price on the stock
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its Outperform rating on Lisi shares, with the target price raised from €27 to €30. After a "quality" 1st quarter, with organic growth of 15%, Oddo BHF anticipates "an equally good 2nd quarter, with organic growth of around 15%, i.e. a similar performance for the half-year as a whole".The analyst expects annual ROC of 95 ME, revised slightly downwards (vs. 100 ME previously +6.5% YoY), translating into MOPC of 5.8% (vs. 6.3% YoY, -50 bp), in line with management's objectives of deteriorating profitability in relative terms.  The main challenge is cost control and the ability to pass on higher costs to sales prices", stresses the broker. For 2024, Oddo BHF leaves unchanged its ROC estimate of 113 ME (+19% YoY), i.e. an MOPC of 6.5% (+70 bp) in line with the consensus.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: OSE IMMUNO :  Invest Securities confirms its recommendation
full_text: OSE Immuno has announced the positive verdict of a futility analysis conducted by the DSMB (Independent Drug Safety Monitoring Board) for its Ph II study in UC (ulcerative colitis) in patients with moderate to severe active disease.  This analysis focused on the first 50 patients to complete the induction phase (10 weeks of treatment), with a total cohort of 150 patients," explains Invest Securities. ' As a reminder, the main results of this trial are expected at the end of the year for the induction phase, with data in the maintenance phase expected in H1 2024. Positive results in UC could re-launch OSE-127 following Servier's decision to surrender rights earlier this year. full_text: On Wednesday, Portzamparc added Esker to its 'High Five' list of five mid-cap stocks specially recommended for purchase by its analysts, bringing the stock to Paris this afternoon.In a note, the brokerage firm hails the document dematerialization specialist's "reassuring" start to the year, reporting "sustained" order intake in the first quarter.Portzamparc also mentions its future growth levers, starting with the prospect of mandatory electronic invoicing in France from the 2024 financial year.The brokerage firm also indicates that it has added Beneteau and Infotel to its list, while excluding Trigano, Fountaine Pajot and Spie.Around 3:30 pm, Esker shares were up by more than 2% on Euronext Paris.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: SOCIETE GENERALE :  Oddo BHF raises its advice and target
full_text: Oddo BHF adjusts its recommendation on Societe Generale shares from 'neutral' to 'outperform', with a price target raised from 29 to 33 euros. The analyst reports that Société Générale shares have significantly underperformed the European banking sector over the past 18 months. Oddo BHF adds: "The change of CEO, with the holding of an investor day on September 18, is boosting interest in the share. The broker believes that, after a difficult 2023, a strong rebound in net income is expected in 2024 (+34%) and 2025, boosting the share's recovery.  We therefore forecast a 63% increase in the Group's NI between 2023 and 2025, with an expected RoTE of around 9% in 2025 (vs. target of 10%)", says the analyst.  The stock is very cheap and should rebound over the next 6/12 months, due to the updated presentation of the Group's strategy, but also to the prospects of a gradual rebound in NI next year', it concludes. title: UBS raises target for SAP to 140 euros - 'Buy'
full_text: ZURICH (dpa-AFX) - Major Swiss bank UBS raised its price target for SAP ahead of the second-quarter reporting season to 140 euros from 130 euros and kept its rating at "buy." Conditions in the software and IT market are unchanged, but more is priced into the shares of industry stocks, analyst Michael Briest wrote in an industry report released Wednesday. The prices are vulnerable to possible disappointments after strong performance, he said. However, he remains positive on SAP, saying the Walldorf-based company is probably making progress with its plans. He adjusted his estimates to reflect new ambitions for 2025. The increased valuation of cloud stocks also leads him to a higher valuation multiple./tih/men  Original study publication date: 07/05/2023 / 03:18 / GMT First disclosure of the original study: 05.07.2023 / 03:18 / GMT

title: Stifel downgrades Vonovia to 'Sell' on debt concerns
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - Investment bank Stifel downgraded Vonovia to "sell" from "hold" and cut its price target to 17.25 euros from 25.00 euros. The party of the German residential real estate companies has come to an abrupt end with the longer rising interest rates, wrote analyst Denese Newton in an industry study available on Wednesday. The next phase is likely to be a prolonged hangover rather than a "civilized after-show party," she added. Loan-to-value ratios could reach dimensions that made refinancing even more difficult. There would then be a risk that larger capital increases would be necessary. In any case, the development could lead to a decade of limited profit growth./tih/gl  Publication of the original study: 05.07.2023 / 01:25 / EDT  First disclosure of the original study: 05.07.2023 / 01:25 / EDT----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: IMERYS :  Oddo BHF remains positive, reduces its target
full_text: Oddo BHF confirms its 'outperform' rating on Imerys shares, with a price target lowered from €60 to €55. With publication of the 2nd quarter due on July 27 after close of trading, Oddo BHF is already anticipating 'a further deterioration in sales volumes'. The analyst points to the unfavorable basis of comparison linked to a very dynamic Q2 2022, amplified by good trends in industrial activities. Against this backdrop, Oddo BHF expects a 14% decline in sales volumes in Q2."In the end, sales should come out at 1,027 ME (-9% L/L, exchange rates -1%, scope 1%)", stresses the broker, who targets unchanged EBITDA for 2023 at 604 ME, but lowers his sales forecast to 3,932 ME vs. 4,258 ME "to take account of more difficult trends". Oddo BHF believes that the share price could come under pressure in the coming days, despite its already difficult stock market performance. Nevertheless, the analyst remains positive: "We believe that the stock has limited downside potential, given its recent poor performance and a recovery in momentum. An opportunity to strengthen at a good price", he adds. Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: LHYFE :  Oddo BHF slightly revises its price target
full_text: Oddo BHF maintains its 'neutral' rating on Lhyfe shares, with a price target lowered from 9 to 8 euros. The analyst reports that management has confirmed the targets set at the IPO a year ago, i.e. installed capacity of 55 MW by 2024 (+10 MW in 2023, then +40 MW in 2024), then 200 MW in 2026, with full impact in 2027.Meanwhile, Oddo believes that FCF will remain negative, with EBITDA expected to be negative until 2026. Management is aiming to reach the EBITDA break-even point in 2026, but the ramp-up will necessarily be long", notes the analyst.In concrete terms, "we have revised downwards our earnings sequence, with sales of around 2 ME (vs. 7.6 ME previously) and EBITDA of -26.4 ME (vs. -21.2 ME previously) for 2023", concludes the broker. title: GETLINK :  J.P. Morgan initiates buy coverage
full_text: On Wednesday, J.P. Morgan initiated coverage of Getlink shares with a Buy recommendation and a two-year price target of 19 euros.In a research note, the analyst praises the diversification of the group, which holds the concession for the Channel Tunnel until 2086, into rail freight (Europorte) and energy infrastructure (ElecLink).The intermediary points out that Getlink shares have largely underperformed the market this year, and are now trading on an Enterprise Value/Ebitda 2024 ratio of 13.5x, compared with its long-term average of 18.5x.J.P. Morgan points out that, at these levels, the share price sufficiently takes into account the uncertainties surrounding the business in the short term, but underestimates the price control from which the Group benefits.Nevertheless, J.P. Morgan considers the stock to be an attractive long-term investment, particularly in view of its exposure to the green growth theme.In an ideal bull case scenario, the stock could reach 22 euros in June 2025, he concludes, corresponding to a potential appreciation of 40%.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: HSBC sees no end to solar boom and advises buy on Wacker Chemie
full_text: LONDON (dpa-AFX) - British investment bank HSBC expects a bright future for solar energy worldwide. Wacker Chemie should also benefit from this, according to an industry report published on Tuesday. Analyst Sean McLoughlin therefore upgraded the share from "Hold" to "Buy" and raised the price target from 150 to 155 euros - which is now almost 22 percent above the current valuation level.      The expert pointed out that the skyrocketing of solar energy is continuing. The International Energy Agency expects higher investment in solar energy than in oil production for the first time in 2023. For this reason, McLoughlin now expects new solar energy plants with a capacity of 344 gigawatts to be built worldwide in the current year - 44 percent more than in 2022 and 18 percent more than he had previously expected. By 2026, this figure should already rise to 500 gigawatts. As recently as 2010, global demand was only 20 gigawatts, he recalled.      A new wave of supply for polysilicon from China has removed a major supply bottleneck and caused solar module prices to drop significantly since the beginning of the year, fueling demand, McLoughlin pointed out. Discussions at this year's Intersolar industry trade show showed that the industry expects polysilicon prices to stabilize at a low level and solar module prices to continue to fall, he said.      According to the expert, there is no end in sight to the overcapacity, as the five leading solar module manufacturers alone are planning to invest USD 7.5 billion in additional production capacity in the current year. In addition, he said, there are efforts to increase domestic production in the U.S. and Europe due to concerns about energy security, which should put even more pressure on polysilicon prices and make them increasingly independent of China.      McLoughlin also justified the Wacker Chemical upgrade by citing plans in Germany to support solar industry production. Meanwhile, his favorite sector companies in Asia are China's JinkoSolar, Longi, Flat Glass and Sungrow, all of whose shares he also rates "buy."/gl/tih/men  Publication of the original study: 03.07.2023 / 15:32 / GMT  First disclosure of the original study: 03.07.2023 / 21:02 / GMT      HSBC rates such stocks as "Buy" with a target price more than 20 percent above the current price. title: ARGAN :  Degroof Petercam lowers target
full_text: Degroof Petercam on Monday maintained its buy recommendation on Argan, but lowered its target price on the stock from €94 to €81 to take into account a higher weighted average cost of capital (WACC) assumption.In a research note, the analyst highlights a company with a "solid growth engine" in the logistics market and good development prospects.Nevertheless, he expresses concern about the spectre of a forthcoming debt refinancing, a factor he believes could penalize future earnings growth.After several years of steadily building up its asset portfolio, Argan has decided to focus on reducing its debt, and to finance its new projects through the disposal of old ones, he points out.Degroof Petercam concludes that the management team has set itself the target of reducing its net debt-to-equity ratio (LTV) to around 40%, compared with 45% at the end of 2022.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: SAINT-GOBAIN :  Oddo BHF reiterates its recommendation on the stock
full_text: On June 30, Saint-Gobain held an analysts' lunch with Benoit Bazin, CEO, and Sreedhar N. CFO. Following this meeting, Oddo BHF confirms its Outperform recommendation on the share, with a target price of E70.' Benoit Bazin doesn't want to 'build an empire', but rather focus on sustainable construction (growth, cash and ROCE) while respecting high CSR criteria' says Oddo BHF. The analyst also points out that share buybacks will continue, especially at this EBITDA multiple level, in excess of 500 ME per year.  The advantage of the North American market lies in its greater consolidation (listed companies) than the European market, which is still largely owned by families whose criteria are less focused on ROCE," stresses the analyst. Oddo BHF continues to believe that Saint-Gobain still has the potential to surprise, particularly in the first half of the year. The consensus is for a 10% fall in annual EBIT, compared with a 5/10% rise for Sika and even >10% for Holcim. The research firm now expects a decline of 6%, i.e. 4% above market expectations.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. full_text: UBS remains neutral on EssilorLuxottica, but has lowered its target price to E187 (from E195).The analyst believes that inflation should lead to a pause in margin expansion in the first half of the year.' title: Stifel raises KWS Saat to 'Buy' and target to 74 euros
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - Investment bank Stifel has upgraded KWS Saat from "hold" to "buy" and raised its price target from 72 to 74 euros. In the chemical sector, investors must prepare for further profit warnings, analyst Andreas Heine wrote in a study on Monday. Market expectations for 2024 appeared too optimistic. Heine therefore prefers companies with comparatively reliable earnings growth, as a cyclical recovery is likely to drag on. In addition to KWS Saat, he also recommends Givaudan./ag/edh  Publication of the original study: 03.07.2023 / 01:05 / EDT First disclosure of the original study: 03.07.2023 / 01:05 / EDT
